1
00:00:56,931 --> 00:00:59,225
<i>我们的故事开始于</i>
<i>Our story begins high over New York City...</i>


2
00:00:59,267 --> 00:01:00,977
一间纽约市的属于也许是这个世界上最不像天才的…
<i>in the luxurious penthouse apartment...</i>

3
00:01:01,019 --> 00:01:04,397
 楼顶豪华别墅里。
<i>of perhaps the most unlikely genius the world has ever known.</i>

4
00:01:06,024 --> 00:01:08,318
对不起，被你撞见我在做瑜伽了。
Sorry. You caught me doing my yoga.

5
00:01:08,360 --> 00:01:11,196
你以为我是一只倒过来的狗？
You were expecting downward dog, perhaps?

6
00:01:12,280 --> 00:01:14,991
我的名字是皮博迪。
My name is Mr. Peabody.

7
00:01:15,033 --> 00:01:17,160
因为我们将会相处一段时间…
And since we're going to be spending some time together...

8
00:01:17,202 --> 00:01:19,371
所以我愿意先和你介绍一下我自己。
I'd like to tell you a little bit about myself.

9
00:01:19,412 --> 00:01:20,705
当我还是一只小狗的时候…
You see, ever since I was a pup...

10
00:01:20,747 --> 00:01:22,582
很显然我与众不同。
it was clear that I was different.

11
00:01:24,626 --> 00:01:26,127
我曾试着融进狗群…
<i>I tried to fit in...</i>

12
00:01:26,169 --> 00:01:27,253
不，谢了。
No, thank you.

13
00:01:27,295 --> 00:01:28,922
但总是做不到。
<i>But never could.</i>

14
00:01:29,422 --> 00:01:32,050
随着我逐渐长大，我见到越来越多的“狗友”……
<i>As I grew, I saw more and more of my littermates...</i>

15
00:01:32,092 --> 00:01:34,761
被新家庭领养了。
<i>being chosen by their new families.</i>

16
00:01:35,470 --> 00:01:38,390
但出于某些原因，我从来没被认领过。
<i>But for some reason, I never was.</i>

17
00:01:40,475 --> 00:01:42,268
来吧小狗狗，去捡回来！
Come on, boy! Fetch the stick!

18
00:01:42,894 --> 00:01:45,063
为什么？你想要我捡回来让你再扔一次么？
But why? Won't you just throw it again?

19
00:01:45,105 --> 00:01:47,524
这只是一项毫无意义的运动。
It's an exercise in futility.

20
00:01:47,565 --> 00:01:50,193
妈，我不喜欢这只狗。他太冷嘲热讽了。
I don't want this one, Mommy. He's sarcastic.

21
00:01:50,235 --> 00:01:52,362
等等！回来！回来扔树枝啊！
Wait, wait! Come back! Throw the stick.

22
00:01:52,404 --> 00:01:55,240
我会坐着不动，我会后脚站立，我甚至会和你握手！
I'll stay, I'll heel, I'll even shake hands.

23
00:01:55,281 --> 00:01:56,950
汪，汪？
Bark, bark?

24
00:01:56,991 --> 00:02:00,286
所以，没有我自己的家庭…
<i>So, without a family of my own...</i>

25
00:02:00,328 --> 00:02:02,789
我投身于知识…
<i>I dedicated myself to the pursuit of knowledge...</i>

26
00:02:03,081 --> 00:02:05,750
文化，还有体育的追求。
<i>culture, and athletics.</i>

27
00:02:07,252 --> 00:02:09,254
我在哈佛获得了学位。
<i>I received my degree at Harvard.</i>

28
00:02:09,295 --> 00:02:11,131
史上第一只狗狗，是的。
<i>Vale-dog-torian, of course.</i>

29
00:02:12,340 --> 00:02:15,385
接着，我又投身于造福人类。
And then, I devoted myself to helping mankind.

30
00:02:15,427 --> 00:02:18,096
我开阔了可再生能源新技术。
<i>I pioneered new techniques in alternative energy.</i>

31
00:02:21,641 --> 00:02:24,102
解决了国际争端。
<i>Resolved geopolitical conflicts around the globe.</i>

32
00:02:27,439 --> 00:02:28,565
而且在我的空闲时间…
<i>And in my spare time...</i>

33
00:02:28,606 --> 00:02:31,234
我发明了打拳头式招呼，下卧式撒尿，可撕扯裤子…
<i>I invented the fist bump, planking, tearaway pants...</i>

34
00:02:31,276 --> 00:02:32,402
自动调音…
<i>Auto-Tune...</i>

35
00:02:32,444 --> 00:02:34,070
背部翱骊（一种滑板动作）…
<i>the backside ollie...</i>

36
00:02:34,112 --> 00:02:35,238
还有准巴舞。
<i>and Zumba.</i>

37
00:02:42,203 --> 00:02:45,999
但最令我自豪的是我的儿子，谢尔曼。
But what I'm most proud of is my son, Sherman.

38
00:02:46,041 --> 00:02:48,126
嗨，皮博迪先生。
Hi, Mr. Peabody.

39
00:02:49,669 --> 00:02:52,005
你告诉他们WABAC了吗？
Have you told them about the WABAC?

40
00:02:52,047 --> 00:02:54,257
我刚好要说。
I was just getting to that.

41
00:02:54,299 --> 00:02:57,761
当我收养谢尔曼的时候，我发誓要成为最好的父亲。
When I adopted Sherman, I vowed to be the best father I could be.

42
00:02:57,802 --> 00:03:01,931
为了让他对这个世界的神奇做好准备，无论是过去或者现在。
To prepare him for all the wonders of the world, present and past.

43
00:03:01,973 --> 00:03:06,311
谢尔曼给了我灵感让我发明我一生中最棒的东西…
And so, Sherman inspired the greatest invention of my life...

44
00:03:06,895 --> 00:03:09,314
时光机器。
a time machine.

45
00:03:15,487 --> 00:03:19,366
当然了，时间旅行是有点难以预料的。
Of course, time travel can be a bit unpredictable.

46
00:03:19,407 --> 00:03:22,202
在时空穿梭的路上一定会有一点磕碰。
There are bound to be a few mishaps along the way.

47
00:03:22,243 --> 00:03:25,705
打个比方，倾斜的比萨斜塔一开始并不是倾斜的。
Let's just say, the Leaning Tower of Pisa wasn't always leaning.

48
00:03:25,747 --> 00:03:28,166
但是没有别的事情比亲身经历历史事件更赞的了。
But there's nothing like learning the lessons of history firsthand.

49
00:03:28,208 --> 00:03:29,292
对不，谢尔曼？
Right, Sherman?

50
00:03:29,334 --> 00:03:31,336
我们今天要去哪里呢，皮博迪先生？
Where are we going today, Mr. Peabody?

51
00:03:31,378 --> 00:03:32,962
不是“哪里”，谢尔曼。
Not "where," Sherman.

52
00:03:33,004 --> 00:03:34,839
应该是“什么时候”。
"When."

53
00:03:48,603 --> 00:03:50,980
法国大革命——1789


这是我见过的最大的房子了！
<i>This is the biggest house I've ever seen!</i>

54
00:03:51,022 --> 00:03:54,025
这是凡尔赛宫，玛丽·安托瓦内特的家。
<i>It's the Palace of Versailles, home of Marie Antoinette.</i>

55
00:03:54,067 --> 00:03:56,653
你知道的，她有一件事最出名。
<i>You know, she was mostly famous for one thing.</i>

56
00:03:56,695 --> 00:03:58,029
蛋糕！
Cake!

57
00:03:58,071 --> 00:04:01,366
我爱死蛋糕了！
I love cake so much.

58
00:04:05,453 --> 00:04:08,373
看来玛丽·安托瓦内特真的超喜欢蛋糕，皮博迪先生。
Marie Antoinette sure likes cake, Mr. Peabody.

59
00:04:08,415 --> 00:04:09,666
确实。
Indeed, she does.

60
00:04:09,708 --> 00:04:11,668
玛丽·安托瓦内特对一切涂有糖霜的东西…
Marie was a womanwith a prodigious appetite...

61
00:04:11,710 --> 00:04:13,837
都有特别惊人的胃口。
for all things covered with frosting.

62
00:04:13,878 --> 00:04:17,173
但她在吃的方面花的那么多钱使她成了社会批判的众矢之的。
But her expensive tastes made her the target of much criticism.

63
00:04:17,215 --> 00:04:19,009
- Why?       - Because, Sherman...    
-为什么？    - 因为，谢尔曼…

64
00:04:19,050 --> 00:04:22,220
在玛丽的统治下，法国的老百姓都极度贫穷。
during Marie's reign, the common people of France were exceedingly poor.

65
00:04:23,221 --> 00:04:24,347
你有面包么？
You've got any bread?

66
00:04:24,389 --> 00:04:27,225
没有！我极度贫穷！
No! I'm exceedingly poor.

67
00:04:27,809 --> 00:04:29,352
现在我们可以吃些蛋糕了吗？
Now, can we have some cake?

68
00:04:29,394 --> 00:04:30,520
好的。（法语）
<i>Mais, oui.</i>

69
00:04:30,562 --> 00:04:33,189
哦，对了，对不起。
Oh, yeah, sorry.

70
00:04:33,231 --> 00:04:34,858
“请问”我们可不可以吃些蛋糕？
"May we" have some cake?

71
00:04:34,899 --> 00:04:36,067
是的是的！
<i>Mais, oui!</i>

72
00:04:36,568 --> 00:04:38,194
也许她的头发盖住了耳朵让她听不到我说话。
Maybe she can't hear me through the hair.

73
00:04:38,236 --> 00:04:40,447
谢尔曼，女王的意思是…
Sherman, what the queen means is...

74
00:04:41,448 --> 00:04:44,117
让他们吃蛋糕吧！
Let them eat cake!

75
00:04:46,578 --> 00:04:49,873
当女王听到巴黎的贫穷人民甚至没钱卖面包时…
When the queen heard the poor of Paris could not even buy bread...

76
00:04:49,914 --> 00:04:52,208
她只是说，“给他们吃点蛋糕吧！”
she said, "Let them eat cake."

77
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:53,293
不！
No!

78
00:04:53,335 --> 00:04:54,586
我亲耳听到的！
I heard it myself.

79
00:04:54,627 --> 00:04:55,948
-这是丑闻！              -这是暴行！
- It's a scandal!     - It's an outrage!   

80
00:04:55,962 --> 00:04:57,130
把女王赶下台！
Down with the queen!

81
00:04:57,172 --> 00:04:58,173
废掉君主制！
Down with the monarchy!

82
00:04:58,590 --> 00:04:59,758
等等！
Wait!

83
00:04:59,799 --> 00:05:01,426
是什么蛋糕？
What kind of cake?

84
00:05:08,850 --> 00:05:11,478
真是个美妙的派对，亲爱的女王。
Smashing party, Your Majesty.

85
00:05:11,519 --> 00:05:14,147
但现在，我担心谢尔曼和我应该…
But now, I'm afraid Sherman and I must be...

86
00:05:14,189 --> 00:05:16,566
谢尔曼？谢尔曼？
Sherman? Sherman?

87
00:05:16,608 --> 00:05:18,318
谢尔曼！
Sherman!

88
00:05:20,278 --> 00:05:21,946
谢尔曼？
Sherman?

89
00:05:24,157 --> 00:05:26,785
谢尔曼！这里，谢尔曼。
Sherman! Here, Sherman.

90
00:05:27,327 --> 00:05:28,745
嗨，皮博迪先生。
Hey, Mr. Peabody.

91
00:05:28,787 --> 00:05:30,622
你在这干嘛？
What are you doing in here?

92
00:05:30,663 --> 00:05:31,998
试试这些蛋糕。
Trying these other cakes.

93
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:36,378
这个大的蛋糕涂满了奶油和草莓…
There's one in here with whipped cream and strawberries that's...

94
00:05:36,878 --> 00:05:39,422
-太棒了！                 -谢尔曼…
- pretty fantastic!      - Sherman...

95
00:05:39,464 --> 00:05:43,426
你忘了我告诉过你为什么在这期间要跟紧我？
don't you remember why I told you to stay close to me during the French Revolution?

96
00:05:43,468 --> 00:05:45,303
因为在法国大革命之后…
Because after the French Revolution...

97
00:05:45,345 --> 00:05:47,097
-一切都会被毁掉？      -差不多。
- it was gonna rain?   - Close.


98
00:05:47,138 --> 00:05:49,599
我说过，“在法国大革命到来时…
I said, "After the French Revolution comes...

99
00:05:49,641 --> 00:05:51,810
会是一场腥风血雨！”
the Reign of Terror!"

100
00:05:57,315 --> 00:06:00,151
把贵族都给抓起来！
Round up the aristocrats.

101
00:06:14,666 --> 00:06:17,711
女王和她的贵族狗友…
The queen and her aristocratic cronies...

102
00:06:17,752 --> 00:06:20,630
要为他们的暴政付出代价！
must pay the price for their gluttony.

103
00:06:20,672 --> 00:06:23,717
我们要把他们像狗一样都杀光！
We will slaughter them like the dogs they are.

104
00:06:23,758 --> 00:06:25,677
先从这只开始！
Starting with this one!

105
00:06:26,177 --> 00:06:27,178
皮博迪先生！
Mr. Peabody!

106
00:06:28,013 --> 00:06:29,472
我应该做什么？
What should I do?

107
00:06:29,514 --> 00:06:32,475
什么都不用做，谢尔曼。站在那儿别动。
Nothing, Sherman. Just stay right there.

108
00:06:32,517 --> 00:06:33,810
但是，皮博迪先生！
But, Mr. Peabody!

109
00:06:33,852 --> 00:06:35,812
一切都会没事的，谢尔曼。
Everything is going to be fine, Sherman.

110
00:06:35,854 --> 00:06:38,523
站在那儿就好。
Just stay right there.

111
00:06:44,904 --> 00:06:46,114
砍了他的头！
Off with his head!

112
00:06:49,284 --> 00:06:51,244
皮博迪先生
Mr. Peabody!

113
00:06:57,375 --> 00:06:59,002
一个哈密瓜？
A cantaloupe?

114
00:06:59,044 --> 00:07:00,920
最低等的水果。
The lowest of the fruits.

115
00:07:00,962 --> 00:07:04,591
竟然有人敢用这个瓜来耍我？
Who dares to insult me with this melon?

116
00:07:08,261 --> 00:07:10,930
抓住那只狗！
Get that dog!

117
00:07:11,556 --> 00:07:14,017
皮博迪先生，你是怎么逃出来的？
Mr. Peabody, how did you escape?

118
00:07:14,059 --> 00:07:15,226
那很简单，谢尔曼。
It's simple, Sherman.

119
00:07:15,268 --> 00:07:17,103
我注意到了沟井盖间的距离…
<i>I noticed the distance between the sewer lids...</i>

120
00:07:17,145 --> 00:07:19,898
算出了一定有一个沟井盖正对着断头台下方…
<i>reasoned that there must be one directly under the guillotine platform...</i>

121
00:07:19,939 --> 00:07:21,540
记住了篮子下面松动的木板…
<i>noted the loose board under the basket...</i>

122
00:07:21,566 --> 00:07:23,943
计算出太阳光在你的眼镜上反射的角度…
<i>computed the angle at which the setting sun
would bounce off your glasses...</i>

123
00:07:23,985 --> 00:07:25,904
暂时照瞎刽子手的眼睛时…
<i>momentarily blinding the executioner...</i>

124
00:07:25,945 --> 00:07:27,906
我看准了这个时机偷来刽子手的哈密瓜…
<i>and chose that moment to swipe the executioner's melon...</i>

125
00:07:27,947 --> 00:07:31,076
哈密瓜的重量让那块松动的木板翻转过来，促成了我的逃脱。
<i>giving me the added weight to tip the boards, facilitating my exit.</i>

126
00:07:31,117 --> 00:07:32,410
那太不可思议了！
That's amazing!

127
00:07:32,452 --> 00:07:33,578
没有这么夸张。
It's not amazing.

128
00:07:33,620 --> 00:07:36,039
我只不过是保住了我的头罢了。
It was just a matter of keeping my head.

129
00:07:36,081 --> 00:07:37,832
哈哈太搞笑了，“保住了你的头。”
"Keeping your head."

130
00:07:38,416 --> 00:07:39,626
笑点在哪？
I don't get it.

131
00:07:39,668 --> 00:07:42,045
他在这里，追上去！
There he is! After them!

132
00:07:42,087 --> 00:07:43,755
这边，谢尔曼，快点！
Come, Sherman, quick!

133
00:07:48,093 --> 00:07:49,761
这水的味道真糟糕！
This water tastes terrible.

134
00:07:49,803 --> 00:07:51,680
有意思的是，这些不是水。
Interestingly, that's not water.

135
00:07:57,102 --> 00:07:58,186
抓住你了！
I've got you now.

136
00:08:00,647 --> 00:08:02,982
你确实抓住我了。罗伯斯庇尔先生（法国大革命时期政治家）。
Indeed you have, <i>Monsieur </i>Robespierre.

137
00:08:03,024 --> 00:08:05,860
你抓人太厉害了。
And what a master of the chase you are.

138
00:08:05,902 --> 00:08:07,070
你注意到了？
You noticed?

139
00:08:07,112 --> 00:08:08,196
当然。
Of course.

140
00:08:08,238 --> 00:08:09,739
像这样让我腹背受敌。
Doubling back on me like that.

141
00:08:09,781 --> 00:08:10,990
真是天才。
That was genius.

142
00:08:11,032 --> 00:08:12,158
谢谢。
Thank you.

143
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:14,244
我只是希望你不要抓走我的小伙伴。
I just hope you don't take my little confederate, here.

144
00:08:14,285 --> 00:08:15,912
我完全靠他了。
I depend on him so completely.

145
00:08:15,954 --> 00:08:17,163
过来这里！
Get over here, you.

146
00:08:17,205 --> 00:08:18,915
糟糕！你太聪明了！
Drats! You're devilishly clever.

147
00:08:18,957 --> 00:08:21,459
我知道。而且我还比你快。
I know. And much quicker than you as well.

148
00:08:21,501 --> 00:08:23,128
但你有比这快吗？
But are you quick enough for this?

149
00:08:23,670 --> 00:08:24,754
看见了吗？多快啊！
See? Quick!

150
00:08:24,796 --> 00:08:26,798
是很快，不过就是不太聪明。
Quick, yes, but not too smart.

151
00:08:27,674 --> 00:08:29,592
另一个哈密瓜！
Another cantaloupe!

152
00:08:29,634 --> 00:08:30,635
你的剑！
Your sword!

153
00:08:31,136 --> 00:08:34,973
好了，谢尔曼，看来考验一只狗的剑术的时候到了。
All right, Sherman, looks like it's time for a little pop quiz in the art of fencing.

154
00:08:35,015 --> 00:08:36,266
开始！
Go!

155
00:08:36,307 --> 00:08:38,810
进攻！回避！猛刺！再来一次！
Attack! Parry! Thrust! Repeat!

156
00:08:38,852 --> 00:08:40,478
-不要。  -再刺！
- No.    - Remise!

157
00:08:41,312 --> 00:08:42,439
好小子！
Good boy!

158
00:08:57,537 --> 00:08:58,955
打不中了！
You missed!

159
00:08:58,997 --> 00:09:00,040
我从来不会打不中。
I never miss.

160
00:09:05,086 --> 00:09:06,338
快上来！
Hop on!

161
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:17,057
耶！
Yeah!

162
00:09:17,098 --> 00:09:20,060
-你闻到了吗，谢尔曼？           -不是我放的屁，皮博迪先生。
- Do you smell that, Sherman?   - It wasn't me, Mr. Peabody.

163
00:09:20,101 --> 00:09:21,144
我知道那不是你。
I know it wasn't you.

164
00:09:21,186 --> 00:09:22,979
那是地下供气系统里的沼气。
It's the methane gas in the sewer system.

165
00:09:23,021 --> 00:09:26,149
沼气会在306华氏度爆炸…
And given the fact that it ignites at 306 degrees Fahrenheit...

166
00:09:26,191 --> 00:09:27,317
我们要利用它…
we're about to use it...

167
00:09:27,359 --> 00:09:28,693
炸掉这里！
to blast out of here!

168
00:09:29,444 --> 00:09:31,029
抓紧！
Hang on!

169
00:09:41,289 --> 00:09:43,708
哇哦！
Wow!

170
00:09:50,882 --> 00:09:52,550
降落得挺不错的，对不谢尔曼？
Nice landing, eh, Sherman?

171
00:09:55,220 --> 00:09:57,222
那么，你今天学到了什么，谢尔曼？
So, what did you learn today, Sherman?

172
00:09:57,263 --> 00:09:59,557
法国大革命真是疯了!
That French Revolution was crazy.

173
00:09:59,599 --> 00:10:00,725
何以见得？
How so?

174
00:10:00,767 --> 00:10:03,103
那些伙计把别人的头给砍下来…
All those guys getting their heads chopped off...

175
00:10:03,144 --> 00:10:05,855
却没有人站出来说这是不对的。
and nobody standing up and saying it wasn't right.

176
00:10:05,897 --> 00:10:08,525
而且，玛丽·安托瓦内特明明就可以避免这场革命…
And think, Marie Antoinette could have avoided the whole revolution...

177
00:10:08,566 --> 00:10:11,861
          只需要她发布一项法令把面包分发到穷人中去。
if she'd simply issued an edict to distribute bread amongst the poor.

178
00:10:11,903 --> 00:10:13,697
但是那样做的话，她就没法吃她的点心了。
But then, she couldn't have had her dessert.

179
00:10:13,738 --> 00:10:15,198
为什么不可以，皮博迪先生？
Why not, Mr. Peabody?

180
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:19,619
因为，谢尔曼，鱼和熊掌不可兼得。
Because, Sherman, you can't have your cake and edict, too.

181
00:10:21,413 --> 00:10:22,414
笑点在哪？
I don't get it.

182
00:10:32,924 --> 00:10:35,093
我们明天去哪里，皮博迪先生？
Where are we gonna go tomorrow, Mr. Peabody?

183
00:10:35,135 --> 00:10:38,263
古罗马？狂野西部？1492年？
Ancient Rome? The Wild West? 1492?

184
00:10:38,304 --> 00:10:41,891
不，谢尔曼，这些地方我们一个都不会去。
No, Sherman, tomorrow we won't be going to any of those places.

185
00:10:41,933 --> 00:10:43,101
为什么不？
Why not?

186
00:10:43,143 --> 00:10:44,394
因为明天的冒险…
Because tomorrow's adventure...

187
00:10:44,436 --> 00:10:47,397
需要你自己去搞定。
is one that you're going to be taking all on your own.

188
00:10:47,439 --> 00:10:48,940
什么意思，皮博迪先生？
What do you mean, Mr. Peabody?

189
00:10:48,982 --> 00:10:50,108
你忘了吗？
Don't you remember?

190
00:10:50,150 --> 00:10:51,943
明天你第一天上学。
It's your first day of school.

191
00:10:52,318 --> 00:10:53,862
-我可以开吗？     -当然不行。
- Can I drive?    - Of course not.

192
00:11:04,330 --> 00:11:08,084
要记住，谢尔曼，记住拼写规则。
Remember, Sherman, "i" before "e," except after "c."

193
00:11:08,126 --> 00:11:09,919
我知道了，皮博迪先生。
I know, Mr. Peabody!

194
00:11:09,961 --> 00:11:12,005
还有别忘了加法交换律。
And don't forget about the commutative principle.

195
00:11:12,047 --> 00:11:13,673
2加3等于3加2.
Two plus three equals three plus two.

196
00:11:13,715 --> 00:11:15,508
我知道了，皮博迪先生！
I know, Mr. Peabody!

197
00:11:15,550 --> 00:11:16,676
如果你不得不去厕所的话…
And if you have to go to the bathroom...

198
00:11:16,718 --> 00:11:19,137
只要勇敢举起你的手然后说，“老师我要去厕所。”就好了。
just raise your hand proudly and say, "I have to go."

199
00:11:19,179 --> 00:11:20,972
我会的，皮博迪先生。
I will, Mr. Peabody.

200
00:11:21,014 --> 00:11:23,850
还有要记住，2号铅笔在大多数时候是最标准的…
And remember, the No. 2 pencil is standard for most uses...

201
00:11:23,892 --> 00:11:26,269
但有时候1号铅笔也很好用。
but there are times when a No. 1 comes in handy.

202
00:11:26,311 --> 00:11:27,854
我在你书包里放了一张表格…
I left a little pencil chart in your backpack...

203
00:11:27,896 --> 00:11:30,607
当你不知道要用哪一种的时候就去查它。
which you can consult if it ever becomes a judgment call.

204
00:11:30,648 --> 00:11:33,693
我认为我应付得来！
I think I'll be okay!

205
00:11:36,488 --> 00:11:38,656
-好了，再见了，皮博迪先生。      -等等。   
- Okay, bye, Mr. Peabody.       - Wait.

206
00:11:38,698 --> 00:11:40,019
-放学后见。                  -谢尔曼！
- See you after school.      - Sherman!

207
00:11:40,033 --> 00:11:43,119
我得走了。我还要去社团签到。
I gotta go. I gotta sign up for the clubs.

208
00:11:43,161 --> 00:11:46,956
没有人比我更支持去参加这类增进兄弟情义的组织。
No one is more in favor of participation in fraternal organizations than I.

209
00:11:46,998 --> 00:11:50,210
但在你走之前，我想要你拿着这个。
But before you go, I want you to have this.

210
00:11:50,669 --> 00:11:52,337
谢谢。这是什么？
Thanks. What is it?

211
00:11:52,379 --> 00:11:54,047
一个狗哨子。
A dog whistle.

212
00:11:58,843 --> 00:12:01,346
它坏了，皮博迪先生。
It doesn't work, Mr. Peabody.

213
00:12:02,389 --> 00:12:04,849
它好好的，谢尔曼。
It works fine, Sherman.

214
00:12:04,891 --> 00:12:07,394
它发出的频率只有狗才可以听到。
It's just a frequency only dogs can hear.

215
00:12:08,019 --> 00:12:09,145
太酷了。
Cool.

216
00:12:09,187 --> 00:12:11,856
让这个小纪念品时时刻刻提醒你…
Let that little keepsake be a reminder to you...

217
00:12:11,898 --> 00:12:16,403
无论你面临着什么挑战，无论看起来我距离你多远…
that no matter what challenges you face, no matter how far away I might seem...

218
00:12:16,444 --> 00:12:18,697
再见，皮博迪先生！
Bye, Mr. Peabody!

219
00:12:21,741 --> 00:12:24,119
我都会和你在一起。
I'm with you.

220
00:12:31,584 --> 00:12:33,294
乔治·华盛顿。
<i>George Washington.</i>

221
00:12:34,421 --> 00:12:36,673
谁可以告诉我他是谁？
Who can tell me who he is?

222
00:12:36,715 --> 00:12:38,633
我！我可以！我可以！
Me! I can! I can!

223
00:12:39,634 --> 00:12:40,885
谢尔曼。
Sherman.

224
00:12:40,927 --> 00:12:43,847
美国的第一位总统。
The first president of the United States of America.

225
00:12:43,888 --> 00:12:45,181
真棒。
Good job.

226
00:12:45,223 --> 00:12:48,226
当华盛顿总统还是一个小孩的时候…
And when President Washington was a little boy...

227
00:12:48,268 --> 00:12:51,229
他砍掉了什么树？
what kind of tree did he cut down?

228
00:12:51,271 --> 00:12:52,522
我！我！我！
Me! Me! Me!

229
00:12:52,564 --> 00:12:54,566
-佩妮？         -一棵樱桃树。
- Penny?        - A cherry tree.

230
00:12:54,607 --> 00:12:57,027
-那是瞎编的。       -“瞎编的”是什么树？
- Apocryphal.       - What kind of tree is that?

231
00:12:57,068 --> 00:12:59,446
那不是树。那是一个词。“瞎编的”。
It's not a tree. It's a word. "Apocryphal."

232
00:12:59,487 --> 00:13:01,281
我的意思是这个故事是瞎编的。
It means that story is not true.

233
00:13:01,322 --> 00:13:03,033
-真的？         -是的。
- Really?       - Yeah.

234
00:13:03,074 --> 00:13:05,118
乔治·华盛顿从来没有砍过一棵樱桃树…
George Washington never cut down a cherry tree...

235
00:13:05,160 --> 00:13:06,870
而且他也没有说过“我不可以撒谎”。
and he never said he couldn't lie.

236
00:13:06,911 --> 00:13:09,873
人们编造这些故事出来教小孩说撒谎是不好的…
People made those stories up to teach kids a lesson about lying...

237
00:13:09,914 --> 00:13:10,915
但这些故事本来就不是真的。
but they're not true.

238
00:13:10,957 --> 00:13:14,919
虽说他确实在1776年的圣诞节横渡德拉瓦河。
He did cross the Delaware River, Christmas night, 1776, though.

239
00:13:15,253 --> 00:13:17,630
我爸在今年夏天带我去了那里。我们也渡过那条河。
My dad took me there this summer. We crossed it, too.

240
00:13:17,672 --> 00:13:18,673
不过我摔进去了。
I fell in.

241
00:13:20,842 --> 00:13:24,971
看起来有的人确实懂得历史，对不，佩妮？
Looks like someone really knows their history, huh, Penny?

242
00:13:30,894 --> 00:13:32,645
真高兴认识你们。
It's really great meeting you guys.

243
00:13:32,937 --> 00:13:34,981
也许有一天你们可以到我家来玩。
Maybe you can come over to my house sometime.

244
00:13:35,023 --> 00:13:37,942
我可以给你看我的模型。那是个氢原子模型。
I could bring my new model. It's a hydrogen atom.

245
00:13:37,984 --> 00:13:39,736
你只有一个？
You've only got one, huh?

246
00:13:39,778 --> 00:13:41,821
看来我们得把它劈开才够我们分的了。
Guess we'll have to split it.

247
00:13:43,281 --> 00:13:44,449
好笑话！
Good one!

248
00:13:45,867 --> 00:13:47,285
看着，伙计们。
Check it, guys.

249
00:13:49,621 --> 00:13:51,664
你在吃什么，谢尔曼？
What do you got there, Sherman?

250
00:13:51,706 --> 00:13:53,124
嚼的还是咬的？
Kibbles or bits?

251
00:13:53,166 --> 00:13:57,629
事实上，我在吃小萝卜，有机苹果汁，还有一个吞拿三明治。
Actually, I've got baby carrots, organic apple juice, and a tuna sandwich.

252
00:13:58,672 --> 00:14:01,341
它富含超多的omega-3。
It's super-high in omega-3s.

253
00:14:01,383 --> 00:14:04,094
所以，你吃人吃的东西对不。
So, you eat human food, huh?

254
00:14:04,135 --> 00:14:05,762
当然，为什么不？
Yeah. Why wouldn't I?

255
00:14:05,804 --> 00:14:07,013
因为你是条狗。
Because you're a dog.

256
00:14:07,055 --> 00:14:08,264
我才不是。
No, I'm not.

257
00:14:08,306 --> 00:14:11,601
你当然是。你爸是条狗，所以你也是。
Sure you are. Your dad is a dog, so you're a dog, too.

258
00:14:11,643 --> 00:14:14,104
我想你搞混了。他们父子是收养关系。
I think you're confused. It's an adoptive relationship.

259
00:14:14,145 --> 00:14:15,772
-闭嘴，卡尔。         -好吧。
- Zip it, Carl.       - Okay.

260
00:14:15,814 --> 00:14:17,982
看看。捡回来！
Here, I'll show you. Fetch!

261
00:14:20,485 --> 00:14:22,612
去啊，小狗狗。去吃你的午餐。
Go on, doggy. Go get your lunch.

262
00:14:22,654 --> 00:14:23,697
去啊。
Go on.

263
00:14:23,738 --> 00:14:24,989
去捡啊。
Go get it.

264
00:14:27,075 --> 00:14:28,618
真丢脸。
The humiliation.

265
00:14:28,660 --> 00:14:31,454
谢尔曼，去捡你的东西吃啊。
Sherman, go get your food.

266
00:14:31,496 --> 00:14:33,498
就像一只乖小狗一样。
Make like a good little doggy.

267
00:14:41,006 --> 00:14:42,841
-这是什么？         -这是我的！
- What's this?      - It's mine!

268
00:14:42,882 --> 00:14:45,844
-还给我！            -这是什么？一个哨子？
- Give it back!      - What is it? A whistle?

269
00:14:48,513 --> 00:14:49,889
这破烂东西居然坏了。
Stupid thing doesn't even work.

270
00:14:49,931 --> 00:14:51,558
这是个狗哨子，佩妮。
It's a dog whistle, Penny.

271
00:14:51,599 --> 00:14:54,144
它发出的频率只有狗才听得到。
It operates at a frequency that only dogs can hear.

272
00:14:54,185 --> 00:14:55,895
-回去，卡尔。         -好吧。
- Back up, Carl.      - Okay.

273
00:14:55,937 --> 00:14:58,356
佩妮，那哨子是我的私人财产。
Penny, that whistle is my private property.

274
00:14:58,398 --> 00:15:00,483
-还给我！            -跳啊，狗狗，跳啊。
- Give it back!      - Jump, doggy, jump.

275
00:15:00,525 --> 00:15:01,818
我不是一只狗。
I am not a dog.

276
00:15:01,860 --> 00:15:02,986
来啊，谢尔曼。
Come on, Sherman!

277
00:15:03,028 --> 00:15:05,822
承认吧。你就是一只狗。说啊。
Just admit it. You're a dog. Say it.

278
00:15:05,864 --> 00:15:07,032
让我走！
Let me go!

279
00:15:07,073 --> 00:15:09,659
除非你像一只狗一样求我不然我是不会放手的。
Not until you beg like a dog.

280
00:15:09,701 --> 00:15:11,578
快啊，谢尔曼，求我啊！
Come on, Sherman. Beg!

281
00:15:11,619 --> 00:15:14,372
开打，开打，开打！
Fight, fight, fight!

282
00:15:15,874 --> 00:15:19,836
      谢尔曼先生，谢谢你收到临时通知后赶来…
Mr. Peabody, thank you for coming in on such short notice...

283
00:15:19,878 --> 00:15:22,172
来讨论一下谢尔曼的问题。
to discuss the problem with Sherman.

284
00:15:22,213 --> 00:15:24,174
没关系的，博迪校长。
It's not a problem at all, Principal Purdy.

285
00:15:24,215 --> 00:15:25,508
我完全考虑过了。
I fully expected this.

286
00:15:25,550 --> 00:15:26,676
-真的？        -是的。
- You did?     - Yes.

287
00:15:26,718 --> 00:15:29,137
而且，和谢尔曼有关的资料，我都准备好了。
And, as with all things Sherman-related, I prepared for it.

288
00:15:29,179 --> 00:15:32,140
这有一份课程表写清楚了谢尔曼通过的高等预科课程…
Here's a curriculum that takes Sherman's advanced preparation into account...

289
00:15:32,182 --> 00:15:33,808
但绝对不会要求你安排谢尔曼在学校跳一级或更高。
but won't require you to have him skip one or more grades.

290
00:15:33,850 --> 00:15:34,934
皮博迪先生…
Mr. Peabody...

291
00:15:34,976 --> 00:15:37,536
这儿有一份预科代数工作表，一张高级阅读清单…
Here are some pre-algebra worksheets, an advanced reading list...

292
00:15:37,562 --> 00:15:41,316
还有一个我创建的网站的链接所以他可以开始学中文了。
and a link to a website I created so he can start studying Mandarin Chinese.

293
00:15:41,358 --> 00:15:43,026
是的中文，毕竟，中文是有前途的语言。
It is, after all, the language of the future.

294
00:15:43,068 --> 00:15:44,110
皮博迪先生！
Mr. Peabody!

295
00:15:44,152 --> 00:15:46,279
我也可没有说他不应该学法语，博迪校长。
I'm not saying he shouldn't study French, too, Principal Purdy.

296
00:15:46,321 --> 00:15:47,530
我是说他两样都可以学。
I'm saying have him do both.

297
00:15:47,572 --> 00:15:48,698
皮博迪先生！
Mr. Peabody!

298
00:15:48,740 --> 00:15:50,408
什么？这样还不够？斯瓦希里语（坦桑尼亚的官方语言）？
What? Not enough? Swahili?

299
00:15:52,410 --> 00:15:54,162
谢尔曼今天和人打架了。
Sherman got into a fight today.

300
00:15:54,871 --> 00:15:56,081
哦，天哪。
Oh, dear.

301
00:15:56,915 --> 00:15:58,375
保险起见…
Pictures were taken...

302
00:15:58,416 --> 00:16:00,585
我给他们拍了照片。
for insurance purposes.

303
00:16:07,926 --> 00:16:09,678
他咬了她。
He bit her.

304
00:16:10,553 --> 00:16:15,058
我不得不说，这看起来对你很不利啊，皮博迪先生。
I must say, it doesn't look good for you, Mr. Peabody.

305
00:16:15,100 --> 00:16:18,311
毕竟，你只是一条狗。
After all, you are a dog.

306
00:16:18,353 --> 00:16:20,313
斗胆问一句，你说谁？
Who, may I ask, are you?

307
00:16:20,355 --> 00:16:23,983
我是古宁恩夫人，来自儿童安全和保护局。
I am Ms. Grunion from the Bureau of Child Safety and Protection.

308
00:16:24,025 --> 00:16:27,779
根据法律我们都会联系他们…在…
We're required by law to contact them whenever there's an...

309
00:16:28,780 --> 00:16:29,781
有意外的时候。
incident.

310
00:16:30,448 --> 00:16:33,076
谢尔曼从来就没有做过这样的事情。
Sherman has never done anything like this before.

311
00:16:33,118 --> 00:16:34,744
我相信他一定有他的理由。
I'm sure he must have had a reason.

312
00:16:34,786 --> 00:16:36,705
是的，那个女生确实有点霸道…
Well, the girl was being a bit of a bully...

313
00:16:36,746 --> 00:16:38,081
安静，博迪！
Quiet, Purdy!

314
00:16:38,123 --> 00:16:40,500
小孩子有点打闹是正常的。
It's normal for children to tease.

315
00:16:40,542 --> 00:16:43,169
但不正常的是他们咬人。
It's not normal for them to bite.

316
00:16:43,211 --> 00:16:46,006
显然，他咬人是因为被惹恼了。
Clearly, it's because of how he's being raised.

317
00:16:46,047 --> 00:16:51,678
但在我看来，一只狗永远都不可能成为一个小男孩合适的父亲。
In my opinion, a dog can never be a suitable parent to a little boy.

318
00:16:51,720 --> 00:16:53,096
我必须指出，古宁恩夫人…
I must point out, Ms. Grunion...

319
00:16:53,138 --> 00:16:56,266
我是根据法律获得了谢尔曼的抚养权。
that I won the right to adopt Sherman in a court of law.

320
00:16:56,307 --> 00:16:59,060
法律也可以撤销你的抚养权。
And the court can take it away from you.

321
00:16:59,811 --> 00:17:03,773
明晚我会上你家去进行一项调查。
I'll be coming to your home tomorrow evening to conduct an investigation.

322
00:17:03,815 --> 00:17:07,569
如果我发现，无论是在哪一方面，你不称职的话…
If I discover that you are, in any way, an unfit parent...

323
00:17:07,610 --> 00:17:11,322
我可以预见你对谢尔曼的抚养权将会被撤销。
I will see to it Sherman is removed from your custody.

324
00:17:16,619 --> 00:17:18,121
永远地。
Permanently.

325
00:17:18,663 --> 00:17:21,958
我希望我已经说得够清楚了的。
I hope I've made myself clear.

326
00:17:25,587 --> 00:17:26,755
够清楚的了。
Crystal.

327
00:17:28,840 --> 00:17:31,593
很抱歉我咬了她，皮博迪先生。
I'm sorry I bit her, Mr. Peabody.

328
00:17:31,634 --> 00:17:33,136
我再也不会那样做了。
I won't do it again.

329
00:17:33,178 --> 00:17:34,763
你已经受罚了，当然不会再做了。
You're darn tooting you won't do it again.

330
00:17:34,804 --> 00:17:37,807
这种随意暴力是完全不能被接受的。
This kind of wanton violence is totally unacceptable.

331
00:17:37,849 --> 00:17:41,102
就算她再怎么坏，你也要以甘地为榜样。
And rather uncharacteristic, given how you feel about Mr. Gandhi.

332
00:17:41,811 --> 00:17:43,646
究竟是什么激起了这场矛盾？
What on earth provoked it?

333
00:17:47,317 --> 00:17:49,986
她叫我狗。
She called me a dog.

334
00:17:57,202 --> 00:17:59,496
哦，好吧。
Well, all right then.

335
00:18:01,623 --> 00:18:03,291
很感谢你告诉我。
Thank you for telling me.

336
00:18:04,376 --> 00:18:06,211
睡吧。
Try and get some sleep.

337
00:18:10,382 --> 00:18:12,842
我爱你，皮博迪先生。
I love you, Mr. Peabody.

338
00:18:14,219 --> 00:18:17,180
我也很爱你，谢尔曼。
I have a deep regard for you as well, Sherman.

339
00:20:38,488 --> 00:20:39,739
皮博迪先生…
Mr. Peabody...

340
00:20:39,781 --> 00:20:41,950
你是个获得诺贝尔奖的科学家。
you are a Nobel Prize-winning scientist.

341
00:20:41,991 --> 00:20:43,660
是全美国的领军顾问。
An advisor to heads of state.

342
00:20:43,702 --> 00:20:45,578
是工业的领军人物。
A captain of industry.

343
00:20:45,620 --> 00:20:48,248
为什么你想收养一个男孩？
Why would you want to adopt a boy?

344
00:20:48,289 --> 00:20:49,916
因为，阁下…
Because, Your Honor...

345
00:20:49,958 --> 00:20:55,672
当我第一次见到谢尔曼时，我想起了我是怎么开始我的生活的。
when I found Sherman, it reminded me of how I started out in life.

346
00:20:55,714 --> 00:20:59,676
现在，我想给他那件我一直想拥有的东西。
And now, I want to give him the one thing I always wanted.

347
00:20:59,718 --> 00:21:01,094
一个家。
A home.

348
00:21:01,136 --> 00:21:03,847
你确定你有能力去面对那些抚养一个男孩所需要的…
And you're sure you're capable of meeting all the challenges...

349
00:21:03,888 --> 00:21:05,849
挑战？
of raising a human boy?

350
00:21:05,890 --> 00:21:09,060
所有应该预计的都预料到了，那会有多难？
With all due respect, how hard could it be?

351
00:21:11,062 --> 00:21:12,355
那么非常好。
Very well, then.

352
00:21:12,397 --> 00:21:14,524
如果一个男孩可以收养一只狗…
If a boy can adopt a dog...

353
00:21:14,566 --> 00:21:18,236
为什么一只狗就不能收养一个男孩？
I see no reason why a dog cannot adopt a boy.

354
00:21:22,407 --> 00:21:25,660
-爸爸！        -不，谢尔曼，不要“爸爸”。
- Da-da!       - No, Sherman, not "Da-da."

355
00:21:25,702 --> 00:21:28,038
你要叫我“皮博迪先生。”
You shall call me "Mr. Peabody."

356
00:21:28,079 --> 00:21:30,749
或者，更简洁一点，“皮博迪”就行了。
Or, in less formal moments, simply "Peabody."

357
00:21:32,250 --> 00:21:33,418
对了。
That's right.

358
00:21:33,752 --> 00:21:35,253
皮爸爸！
"Mr. Pea-baba."

359
00:22:17,796 --> 00:22:20,256
-你在煮什么呢，皮博迪先生？          -没什么。
- What's cooking, Mr. Peabody?       - Nothing much.

360
00:22:20,298 --> 00:22:23,593
只是几只太平洋大蟹加上一点百香果酱料。
Just a little Dungeness crab with a passion-fruit basil concassé.

361
00:22:23,635 --> 00:22:25,720
一些杜松果大小的鹌鹑。
Some truffled quails in a juniper-berry reduction.

362
00:22:25,762 --> 00:22:27,722
还有火焰冰激凌。
And Baked Alaska.

363
00:22:27,764 --> 00:22:30,433
哇哦！今天是什么特别的日子么？
Wow! Is todaysome kind of special occasion?

364
00:22:30,475 --> 00:22:31,518
猜猜看。
You could say.

365
00:22:31,559 --> 00:22:34,396
-今天不是我的生日。            -没错，不是。
- It's not my birthday.        - No, it isn't.

366
00:22:34,437 --> 00:22:36,940
-也不是你的生日。                -又对了。
- It's not your birthday.        - Right again.

367
00:22:36,981 --> 00:22:39,109
今天是父亲节对不？
It's not Father's Day. Is it?

368
00:22:39,150 --> 00:22:41,486
错了。今天不是父亲节。
Nope. It's not Father's Day.

369
00:22:42,112 --> 00:22:44,072
是不是总统又要来和我们一起吃饭了？
Is the president coming to dinner again?

370
00:22:44,114 --> 00:22:45,907
-不是。    -哦。
- No.      - Oh.

371
00:22:46,282 --> 00:22:47,742
那么，谁要来和我们一起吃晚餐？
So, who's coming to dinner?

372
00:22:47,784 --> 00:22:50,286
可以这么说，如果这场饭吃得顺利的话…
Let's just say, if the evening is a success...

373
00:22:50,328 --> 00:22:52,997
我们就可以把“咬人”这件事抛到后脑勺去。
we can put this whole "biting" business behind us.

374
00:23:00,088 --> 00:23:02,882
彼得逊一家！欢迎！
The Petersons! Welcome.

375
00:23:02,924 --> 00:23:05,385
看吧，它只是条狗。              -保尔！
- So, he's literally a dog.     - Paul!

376
00:23:05,427 --> 00:23:06,553
没事，没关系。
No, that's all right.

377
00:23:06,594 --> 00:23:09,347
但是我更喜欢叫我，“受过教育的狗”。
Although, I prefer "literate dog."

378
00:23:09,389 --> 00:23:10,640
真有趣！
That's funny.

379
00:23:10,682 --> 00:23:12,017
这不有趣么，保尔？
Isn't that funny, Paul?

380
00:23:13,685 --> 00:23:15,729
他平时不喜欢笑。
He's not a big laugher.

381
00:23:15,770 --> 00:23:18,106
你们在收到通知后过来我们真的很荣幸。
We're so delighted you could make it on such short notice.

382
00:23:18,148 --> 00:23:19,524
对不对啊，谢尔曼？
Aren't we, Sherman?

383
00:23:20,191 --> 00:23:22,318
对不对啊，谢尔曼？
Aren't we, Sherman?

384
00:23:22,360 --> 00:23:25,822
是啊，我们将会很享受今晚的晚餐，绝对地。
Yeah, we're interested in what's going on, that's for sure.

385
00:23:25,864 --> 00:23:27,824
和佩妮打招呼，谢尔曼。
Say hello to Penny, Sherman.

386
00:23:27,866 --> 00:23:29,325
你好，佩妮。
Hi, Penny.

387
00:23:29,617 --> 00:23:31,119
你好，谢尔曼。
Hello, Sherman.

388
00:23:31,161 --> 00:23:34,581
现在，为什么不带佩妮去看一下你的矿石藏品呢？
Now, why don't you go show Penny your mineral collection, Sherman?

389
00:23:34,622 --> 00:23:37,876
她肯定会觉得你的那些晶体很神奇的。
I'm sure she'll find those new geodes of yours fascinating.

390
00:23:38,626 --> 00:23:39,961
过来吧。
Come on.

391
00:23:42,380 --> 00:23:45,175
我很高兴你接受了我的邀请。
I am so glad you accepted my invitation.

392
00:23:45,216 --> 00:23:48,678
现在，孩子们可以在古宁恩夫人到来前解决他们的问题。
Now, the kids can resolve their differences before Ms. Grunion arrives.

393
00:23:48,720 --> 00:23:51,097
你喊错对象了，狗先生。事实上…
You're barking up the wrong tree, mister. In fact...

394
00:23:51,139 --> 00:23:53,516
要不是我的老婆佩蒂求情，我早就对你提出控告了。
if it weren't for Patty, I would have pressed charges already.

395
00:23:53,558 --> 00:23:54,976
而且我还得告诉你，皮博迪先生。
And I have to tell you, Peabody...

396
00:23:55,018 --> 00:23:58,188
就我的女儿而言，没有什么事比得上…
where my daughter is concerned, nothing is more important than...

397
00:23:58,229 --> 00:24:00,690
你好。当然，我接受你的采访。
Hello. Sure, I'll take a survey.

398
00:24:09,699 --> 00:24:11,326
一切还好吗？
Everything going swimmingly?

399
00:24:12,911 --> 00:24:15,455
你干嘛不告诉我她要上这儿来？
Why didn't you tell me she was coming over here?

400
00:24:15,497 --> 00:24:16,897
因为我不想让你担心。
Because I didn't want you to worry.

401
00:24:17,749 --> 00:24:20,043
好吧，其实我是不想听你唠叨！
Okay, because I didn't want to listen to your bellyaching.

402
00:24:20,085 --> 00:24:22,671
谢谢你很诚实。
Thank you for your honesty.

403
00:24:22,712 --> 00:24:23,713
不用谢。
You're welcome.

404
00:24:23,755 --> 00:24:26,549
我不知道你想要我们在这儿做什么。
I don't know what you think we're supposed to do in here anyway.

405
00:24:26,591 --> 00:24:28,134
她恨我。
She hates me.

406
00:24:28,176 --> 00:24:30,345
分享你的兴趣。讲个小笑话。
Share your interests. Tell a witty anecdote.

407
00:24:30,387 --> 00:24:31,554
皮博迪先生…
Mr. Peabody...

408
00:24:31,596 --> 00:24:33,139
我恨她。
I hate her.

409
00:24:33,181 --> 00:24:35,183
谢尔曼，每一段友好的关系…
Sherman, every great relationship...

410
00:24:35,225 --> 00:24:38,103
都是从一段矛盾开始的，而且随着时间的推移这种关系会更进一步发展。
starts from a place of conflict, and evolves into something richer.

411
00:24:39,854 --> 00:24:41,189
祝你好运。
<i>Bonne chance.</i>

412
00:24:42,399 --> 00:24:43,692
好好干。
Make it work.

413
00:24:44,359 --> 00:24:45,944
别告诉她WABAC的事。
But don't tell her about the WABAC.

414
00:24:49,698 --> 00:24:52,784
想都别想。
Don't even think about it.

415
00:25:06,965 --> 00:25:08,883
皮博迪着太美妙了！
Peabody, that was amazing!

416
00:25:09,134 --> 00:25:11,094
保尔，这不是很神奇吗？
Paul, wasn't that amazing?

417
00:25:11,136 --> 00:25:12,470
我更喜欢摇滚乐。
I'm more into rock-'n'-roll.

418
00:25:18,435 --> 00:25:19,811
我指的是弗拉门科民歌（一种西班牙民歌）。
I meant flamenco.

419
00:25:26,776 --> 00:25:27,777
风笛？
Bagpipes?

420
00:25:28,778 --> 00:25:30,071
迪吉里杜管（澳大利亚土著使用的一种乐器）。
Didgeridoo.

421
00:25:33,658 --> 00:25:34,659
锡塔尔琴（印度的一种大弦弹拨乐器）。
Sitar.

422
00:25:34,951 --> 00:25:36,244
钢鼓。
Steel drums.

423
00:25:36,286 --> 00:25:37,454
长号。
Trombone.

424
00:25:37,495 --> 00:25:38,913
木琴。
Xylophone.

425
00:25:38,955 --> 00:25:40,081
非洲鼓？
Djembe?

426
00:25:40,123 --> 00:25:41,291
气笛风琴。
Calliope.

427
00:25:41,332 --> 00:25:42,917
双簧管。 短笛。
Oboe. Piccolo.

428
00:25:42,959 --> 00:25:44,544
大号。冬不拉（乐器名）。
Tuba. Dobro.

429
00:25:44,586 --> 00:25:45,879
滑动吹哨。约德尔唱法。
Slide whistle. Yodeling.

430
00:25:45,920 --> 00:25:47,088
手摇风琴。卵形笛。
Hurdy-gurdy. Ocarina.

431
00:25:47,130 --> 00:25:48,465
脚踏式风琴。钢锯。
Harmonium. Musical saw.

432
00:25:48,506 --> 00:25:50,467
你知道不？这也许很赞…
You know what? This has been great...

433
00:25:50,508 --> 00:25:52,719
但都是浪费时间。
but a complete waste of time.

434
00:25:52,761 --> 00:25:55,472
现在咋门去找佩妮然后回家！
Now, let's get Penny and go home!

435
00:25:55,513 --> 00:25:56,639
你还好吗，保尔？
Are you all right, Paul?

436
00:25:56,681 --> 00:25:59,434
我…还行。
I'm... fine.

437
00:25:59,476 --> 00:26:01,061
每当他紧张的时候他都会这样。
This happens whenever he's tense.

438
00:26:01,102 --> 00:26:02,145
保尔，如果我可以的话…
Paul, if I might...

439
00:26:02,187 --> 00:26:03,438
离我远点，皮博迪！
Stay away from me, Peabody!

440
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:05,982
退后！我需要牵引。
Just get back! I need traction.

441
00:26:06,024 --> 00:26:09,110
你可以信任我，保尔。我是个有执照的脊椎指压治疗者。
You can trust me, Paul. I'm a licensed chiropractor.

442
00:26:23,708 --> 00:26:25,168
皮博迪…
Peabody...

443
00:26:25,210 --> 00:26:26,544
我觉得棒极了。
I feel great.

444
00:26:27,879 --> 00:26:29,506
我感觉真的很棒！
I really feel great!

445
00:26:29,547 --> 00:26:31,800
皮博迪，你真神奇的。
Peabody, you're a miracle worker.

446
00:26:33,718 --> 00:26:35,136
看看我！
Look at me!

447
00:26:35,178 --> 00:26:36,721
我在跳舞！
I'm dancing!

448
00:26:38,890 --> 00:26:40,016
你知道吗，佩妮…
You know, Penny...

449
00:26:40,058 --> 00:26:42,644
西格蒙德·弗洛伊德曾说过如果你不喜欢一个人…
Sigmund Freud says if you don't like a person...

450
00:26:42,686 --> 00:26:46,481
那是因为他们让你想起了你身上让你不喜欢的地方。
it's because they remind you of something you don't like about yourself.

451
00:26:46,523 --> 00:26:48,441
你知道弗洛伊德些什么？
What do you know about Sigmund Freud?

452
00:26:48,483 --> 00:26:49,693
比你认为的还多。
More than you think.

453
00:26:49,734 --> 00:26:52,320
哦当然。就像你知道那些东西…
Sure. Just like you know all that stuff...

454
00:26:52,362 --> 00:26:56,032
说乔治华盛顿没有真的砍过一颗樱桃树。
about George Washington not really cutting down the cherry tree.

455
00:26:56,074 --> 00:26:57,367
真做作。
What a crock.

456
00:26:57,409 --> 00:26:58,535
但那是真的！
But it's true!

457
00:26:58,576 --> 00:27:00,328
-你怎么知道？             -我就是知道！
- How do you know?        - I just know!

458
00:27:00,370 --> 00:27:01,871
-你从树上读到的？                   -没有！
- Did you read it in a book?        - No!

459
00:27:01,913 --> 00:27:03,164
-在电影里看到的？             -没有！
- See it in a movie?          - No!

460
00:27:03,206 --> 00:27:05,458
-你那天才爸爸告诉你的？                   -没有！
- Did your brainiac dad tell you?         - No!

461
00:27:05,500 --> 00:27:06,668
那你怎么知道的，谢尔曼？
So, how do you know, Sherman?

462
00:27:06,710 --> 00:27:08,044
你怎么知道的？
How do you know?

463
00:27:08,086 --> 00:27:09,295
他和说过的。
He told me.

464
00:27:09,337 --> 00:27:10,422
谁和你说过？
Who told you?

465
00:27:10,463 --> 00:27:12,007
乔治华盛顿。
George Washington.

466
00:27:13,758 --> 00:27:15,176
乔治华盛顿？
George Washington?

467
00:27:16,594 --> 00:27:17,846
是的。
Yeah.

468
00:27:18,763 --> 00:27:19,931
骗子。
Liar.

469
00:27:22,934 --> 00:27:24,769
但千万别告诉她WABAC的事。
But don't tell her about the WABAC.

470
00:27:25,937 --> 00:27:27,647
他叫它“WABAC”。
He calls it the "WABAC."

471
00:27:27,689 --> 00:27:29,566
那么，你们去过哪？
So, where have you gone in it?

472
00:27:29,607 --> 00:27:32,193
不是“哪儿”，佩妮，应该是“什么时候”。
Not "where," Penny, "when."

473
00:27:32,235 --> 00:27:34,863
好吧，聪明的小伙，什么时候？
Okay, smart guy, when?

474
00:27:34,904 --> 00:27:39,701
1965年，1776年，1620年…
1965, 1776, 1620...

475
00:27:39,743 --> 00:27:43,580
1492年，1215年，4
1492, 1215, 4.

476
00:27:43,621 --> 00:27:45,707
-我可以回到一个小时前去吗？            -为什么？
- Can it go back to an hour ago?       - Why?

477
00:27:45,749 --> 00:27:48,209
因为我可以回家，假装我病了…
Because I could take it home, pretend to be sick...

478
00:27:48,251 --> 00:27:50,420
然后就可以不来参加这个差劲的晚餐派对了。
and not come to this lame dinner party.

479
00:27:51,087 --> 00:27:53,381
皮博迪先生说过你不应该用WABAC…
Mr. Peabody says you should never use the WABAC...

480
00:27:53,423 --> 00:27:55,592
穿越到你存在的时空。
to travel to a time when you existed.

481
00:27:55,633 --> 00:27:57,719
-何以见得？           -因为那样就会有两个你了。
- How come?           - There would be two of you.

482
00:27:58,762 --> 00:27:59,763
太棒了。
Yeah.

483
00:27:59,804 --> 00:28:01,556
我猜这个世界会接受不了。
I guess the world's not ready for that.

484
00:28:05,310 --> 00:28:06,728
哇哦。
Wow.

485
00:28:08,480 --> 00:28:10,899
现在我们看完了，也许我们得回去了。
Now that we've seen it, maybe we should go back.

486
00:28:10,940 --> 00:28:14,110
你开玩笑么？我们首先要去哪里？
Are you kidding? Where should we go first?

487
00:28:14,152 --> 00:28:17,947
皮博迪先生说除非我长大后不然我就不可以驾驶。
Mr. Peabody says I'm not allowed to drive it till I'm older.

488
00:28:17,989 --> 00:28:20,367
你都按皮博迪先生说的做？
Do you do everything Mr. Peabody says?

489
00:28:20,408 --> 00:28:21,618
是啊。
Yeah.

490
00:28:21,659 --> 00:28:23,578
你知道那造就了你，谢尔曼。
You know what that makes you, Sherman.

491
00:28:23,620 --> 00:28:25,580
一个顺从的儿子？
An obedient son?

492
00:28:25,622 --> 00:28:26,790
才不是。
Nope.

493
00:28:26,831 --> 00:28:28,124
一只狗。
A dog.

494
00:28:42,180 --> 00:28:43,181
好身手。
Nice control.

495
00:28:44,015 --> 00:28:45,642
-看看他！             -接好了，佩蒂！
- Look at him go!     - Take it, Patty!

496
00:28:46,810 --> 00:28:48,019
看着点，保尔！
Heads up, Paul!

497
00:28:48,311 --> 00:28:50,647
冰在这里。走你！
Here you go. Zing!

498
00:28:54,859 --> 00:28:56,611
哦，太棒了。
Oh, yeah.

499
00:28:58,029 --> 00:28:59,155
嘿，看看那个。
Hey, look at that.

500
00:28:59,197 --> 00:29:00,782
这太有趣了！
This is fun!

501
00:29:03,702 --> 00:29:06,663
这种简谱的家庭手工调味品，我喜欢把它叫做…
This is a little homespun concoction I like to call...

502
00:29:08,039 --> 00:29:09,666
“躺在沙滩上的爱因斯坦”。
"Einstein on the Beach."

503
00:29:09,708 --> 00:29:10,959
真棒。
Yummy.

504
00:29:13,461 --> 00:29:14,671
至我们的孩子。
To the kids.

505
00:29:14,713 --> 00:29:16,506
至我们的孩子！
To the kids!

506
00:29:17,382 --> 00:29:18,883
皮博迪先生。
Mr. Peabody.

507
00:29:19,134 --> 00:29:21,678
-谢尔曼？         -我可以跟你说句话么？
- Sherman?        - Can I talk to you a second?

508
00:29:21,720 --> 00:29:22,929
当然可以。
Of course.

509
00:29:22,971 --> 00:29:24,347
抱歉。
Excuse me.

510
00:29:28,810 --> 00:29:30,603
我已经和佩妮的父母聊得来了。
I've really hit it off with Penny's parents.

511
00:29:30,645 --> 00:29:33,815
我想我们可以把这个夜晚打上“不合格的成功”的标签。
I think we can file this night under "Unqualified Success."

512
00:29:33,857 --> 00:29:36,693
是我的话我就不会这么快给这个夜晚打标签了。
I would hold off filing it just yet.

513
00:29:36,735 --> 00:29:39,070
你说的是什么意思？佩妮在哪里？
What do you mean? Where's Penny?

514
00:29:39,988 --> 00:29:41,239
古埃及。
Ancient Egypt.

515
00:29:41,990 --> 00:29:43,742
你们用了WABAC？
You used the WABAC?

516
00:29:44,909 --> 00:29:47,203
怎么了，伙计？我们快喝完了。
What's happening, big guy? We're running low.

517
00:29:50,040 --> 00:29:52,167
我马上就过去，保尔。
I'll be right there, Paul.

518
00:29:52,208 --> 00:29:53,418
你们怎么可以做出这样的事？
How could you do such a thing?

519
00:29:53,460 --> 00:29:54,627
她说我是个骗子…
She called me a liar...

520
00:29:54,669 --> 00:29:57,797
因为我说乔治华盛顿从来没砍过一棵樱桃树。
for saying George Washington never cut down a cherry tree.

521
00:29:57,839 --> 00:30:00,216
所以，你就带她去看乔治华盛顿了？
So, you took her to see George Washington?

522
00:30:00,258 --> 00:30:02,385
是啊。她太喜欢了。
Yeah. She was into it.

523
00:30:02,427 --> 00:30:04,054
嘿，皮老大。
Hey, Pea-buddy.

524
00:30:04,095 --> 00:30:05,180
嘿。
Hey.

525
00:30:05,221 --> 00:30:06,222
佩妮在哪？
Where's Penny?

526
00:30:06,264 --> 00:30:07,849
-玩捉迷藏。                  -拉屎。
- Playing hide-and-seek.     - Pooping.

527
00:30:07,891 --> 00:30:09,726
-拉屎。        -玩捉迷藏。
- Pooping.     - Playing hide and seek.

528
00:30:11,394 --> 00:30:12,395
呃，究竟是哪个？
Well, which is it?

529
00:30:13,938 --> 00:30:15,357
怎么了？
What's going on here?

530
00:30:15,398 --> 00:30:17,192
对啊。怎么了？
Yeah. What's going on here?

531
00:30:17,233 --> 00:30:18,651
-你对佩妮做了什么？                   -佩妮？
- What have you done with Penny?      - Penny?

532
00:30:18,693 --> 00:30:20,320
佩妮？佩妮！
Penny? Penny!

533
00:30:20,362 --> 00:30:22,280
-哦我的天啊！        -我们的女儿在哪里？
- Oh, my gosh!       - Where's our daughter?

534
00:30:23,573 --> 00:30:25,158
这很难说，保尔。
It's hard to say, Paul.

535
00:30:25,200 --> 00:30:30,246
她可以在这里，或这里，或这里，或这里…
She could be here, or here, or here, or here...

536
00:30:30,288 --> 00:30:31,498
或这里。
or here.

537
00:30:33,416 --> 00:30:34,834
那会定住他们。
That will hold them.

538
00:30:34,876 --> 00:30:37,671
这个小花招是我在巴厘岛的乌布的里吉里从一个阁下那里学来的。
I learned that trick from a swami at the Begawan Giri in Ubud, Bali.

539
00:30:37,712 --> 00:30:39,047
快走！
Let's go!

540
00:30:53,061 --> 00:30:56,106
古埃及。法老之地。
Ancient Egypt. Land of the Pharaohs.

541
00:30:56,147 --> 00:30:59,109
人类文明发源进步的指明灯…
A beacon of progress on the horizon of humanity...

542
00:30:59,150 --> 00:31:02,946
但同时也是一个野蛮残暴的社会。
but a cruel and barbarous civilization just the same.

543
00:31:02,987 --> 00:31:05,990
我希望佩妮不会受太多的苦。
I just hope Penny isn't suffering too badly.

544
00:31:18,128 --> 00:31:19,379
我来捡。
I got it.

545
00:31:19,421 --> 00:31:20,755
你在这干嘛？
What are you doing here?

546
00:31:20,797 --> 00:31:22,674
我们来这儿带你回家。
We have come to take you home.

547
00:31:23,341 --> 00:31:25,510
“告密者”在埃及语里怎么说？
What's the Egyptian word for "tattletale"?

548
00:31:26,928 --> 00:31:29,764
但是那个无关紧要。穿好你的衣服，我们要回家了。
But that's beside the point. Get your clothes on, we're going home.

549
00:31:29,806 --> 00:31:31,975
什么时候轮到你来当法老了？
Who died and made you Pharaoh?

550
00:31:32,017 --> 00:31:33,935
现在，快来给我打扮。
Now, bring on the mani-pedi.

551
00:31:34,477 --> 00:31:37,272
看见了吧，皮博迪先生？不可能的事！
See, Mr. Peabody? Impossible!

552
00:31:37,313 --> 00:31:39,149
确实，但看看当一件固定的事物遇上了不可抗力时…
Indeed, but watch what happens...

553
00:31:39,190 --> 00:31:42,444
会发生什么。
when an immovable object meets an irresistible force.

554
00:31:42,902 --> 00:31:43,987
佩妮…
Penny...

555
00:31:44,029 --> 00:31:46,281
过来这里，现在。佩妮，过来！
come here, right now. Penny, come!

556
00:31:46,322 --> 00:31:48,158
我已不再是佩妮了。
I'm not Penny anymore.

557
00:31:48,199 --> 00:31:52,829
现在我是哈特谢普苏特公主，珍贵的尼罗河之花。
Now, I'm Princess Hatsheput, precious flower of the Nile.

558
00:31:52,871 --> 00:31:55,331
也许你确实是“珍贵的”，但如果你认为我们会把你留在这里…
"Precious," perhaps, but if you think we're going to leave you here...

559
00:31:55,373 --> 00:31:57,792
你就肯定会“死在尼罗河里”。
you are most definitely in "de-Nile."

560
00:31:59,294 --> 00:32:00,503
笑点在哪？
I don't get it.

561
00:32:00,545 --> 00:32:01,671
现在，快过来。
Now, come along.

562
00:32:01,713 --> 00:32:03,006
放开她！
Unhand her!

563
00:32:04,174 --> 00:32:06,801
发生什么了，我可爱的沙漠之花？
What's the matter, my sweet little desert blossom?

564
00:32:06,843 --> 00:32:09,179
这些野蛮人在骚扰你吗？
Are these barbarians bothering you?

565
00:32:09,220 --> 00:32:11,931
确实是的。
As a matter of fact, they are.

566
00:32:11,973 --> 00:32:13,516
鞠躬，野蛮人们。
Bow, barbarians.

567
00:32:13,558 --> 00:32:15,685
如你所愿，陛下。
As you wish, Your Highness.

568
00:32:15,727 --> 00:32:17,687
他是谁，皮博迪先生？
Who's that, Mr. Peabody?

569
00:32:17,729 --> 00:32:20,273
他，谢尔曼，是太阳神阿蒙德化身…
That, Sherman, is the living image of Amun...

570
00:32:20,315 --> 00:32:23,526
阿肯那顿之子，这个新王国的第18个国王…
son of Akhenaten, lord of the 18th Dynasty of the New Kingdom...

571
00:32:23,568 --> 00:32:24,819
图坦卡蒙王。
King Tutankhamun.

572
00:32:24,861 --> 00:32:26,696
也被称为“图特王”。
Otherwise known as "King Tut."

573
00:32:26,738 --> 00:32:27,864
我男朋友。
My boyfriend.

574
00:32:27,906 --> 00:32:29,991
图特王是你男朋友？
King Tut is your boyfriend?

575
00:32:30,742 --> 00:32:33,203
你想要把他们的皮剥下来，敷上一层蜂蜜…
Would you like me to have them skinned, covered with honey...

576
00:32:33,244 --> 00:32:35,538
然后放进火蚁坑里吗？
and laid in a pit of fire ants?

577
00:32:36,247 --> 00:32:37,791
你会为了我这么做吗？
You would do that for me?

578
00:32:37,832 --> 00:32:41,044
任何事，我的沙漠之花。这是我给你的结婚礼物。
Anything, my desert flower. Consider it a wedding gift.

579
00:32:41,086 --> 00:32:43,588
什么？你不能嫁给这个人！
What? You can't marry this guy!

580
00:32:43,630 --> 00:32:44,714
为什么不行？
Why not?

581
00:32:44,756 --> 00:32:47,676
首先，他的名字和“屁股”谐音。
For one, his name rhymes with "butt."

582
00:32:47,717 --> 00:32:50,804
我才不管。我要拥有一个大大的隆重的埃及式婚礼。
I don't care. I'm gonna have a big, fat, Egyptian wedding.

583
00:32:50,845 --> 00:32:53,223
给你透露一下，图特王很年轻的时候就死了。
Spoiler alert, King Tut dies young.

584
00:32:53,264 --> 00:32:55,225
你确定你已经考虑过了吗？
Are you sure you've thought this through?

585
00:32:55,266 --> 00:32:57,727
相信我，我都想通了。我要得到一切东西。
Trust me, I've thought it through. I'm getting everything.

586
00:32:57,769 --> 00:32:59,521
皇家天文学家刚刚做了观测…
The royal astronomers have decreed...

587
00:32:59,896 --> 00:33:02,857
明天傍晚是举行婚礼的好时辰。
the wedding must take place tomorrow at dawn.

588
00:33:02,899 --> 00:33:03,983
他是谁？
Who is he?

589
00:33:04,025 --> 00:33:05,360
-他是艾。           -他是你？
- He is Ay.         - He is you?

590
00:33:05,402 --> 00:33:08,238
我是艾。大维齐尔。
I am Ay. The Grand Vizier.

591
00:33:08,613 --> 00:33:10,448
-是的，那就是他的名字。        -哦。
- Yeah, that's his name.       - Oh.

592
00:33:10,699 --> 00:33:13,868
大维齐尔宰相，你可不可以准确地给这位珍贵的公主…
Grand Vizier, would you mind telling the precious princess, here...

593
00:33:13,910 --> 00:33:16,579
描述一下嫁给这位年轻的法老意味着什么。
precisely what it means to marry the young Pharaoh.

594
00:33:16,621 --> 00:33:17,747
荣幸之至。
Gladly.

595
00:33:17,789 --> 00:33:21,084
那意味着她将通过那神圣的仪式取出她的内脏对她进行木乃伊化…
It means she will be bound to him in eternity...

596
00:33:21,126 --> 00:33:25,797
让她来世也属于他…
through the sacred ceremonies of disembowelment and mummification...

597
00:33:26,131 --> 00:33:28,091
就像圣书上描述的那样。
as described in the holy texts.

598
00:33:28,466 --> 00:33:29,926
等一等。
Hold up a second.

599
00:33:29,968 --> 00:33:31,761
有谁可以跟我说更清楚一点？
Can you walk me through that, somebody?

600
00:33:31,803 --> 00:33:35,015
佩妮，他的意思是，当我死的时候，他们也会把你杀死。
What he means, Penny, is that when I die they'll kill you, too.

601
00:33:35,056 --> 00:33:37,851
然后把你的器官挖出来，塞进卡诺皮克坛子里…
And then they'll rip out your organs, stuff them in canopic jars...

602
00:33:37,892 --> 00:33:39,561
然后把剩下的你做成木乃伊。
and then mummify whatever is left.

603
00:33:39,602 --> 00:33:40,770
好的，我现在已经了解了。
Okay, I'm seeing this now.

604
00:33:40,812 --> 00:33:43,606
谢谢你。现在我要和他们一起走了。
Thank you. I'm going to go with them.

605
00:33:44,649 --> 00:33:46,901
现在已经没有回头路了。
There's no turning back now.

606
00:33:46,943 --> 00:33:48,069
往宫殿！
To the palace!

607
00:33:48,111 --> 00:33:49,946
开始准备婚礼！
Let the wedding preparations begin!

608
00:33:50,447 --> 00:33:52,699
皮博迪先生！谢尔曼！
Mr. Peabody! Sherman!

609
00:33:52,741 --> 00:33:53,867
帮帮我！
Do something!

610
00:33:53,908 --> 00:33:54,951
别担心，佩妮！
Don't worry, Penny!

611
00:33:54,993 --> 00:33:56,161
我们会救你的！
We'll save you!

612
00:34:00,749 --> 00:34:02,334
嘿，等等！你们不能就这样…
Hey, wait! You can't just...

613
00:34:03,543 --> 00:34:05,211
把我们丢在这。
leave us here.

614
00:34:05,670 --> 00:34:06,963
皮博迪先生？
Mr. Peabody?

615
00:34:07,005 --> 00:34:08,173
怎么了，谢尔曼？
Yes, Sherman?

616
00:34:08,214 --> 00:34:09,466
我可以牵你的手吗？
Can I hold your hand?

617
00:34:09,507 --> 00:34:11,343
当然可以。
Of course you can.

618
00:34:11,384 --> 00:34:13,970
哦，你的手好冷啊，皮博迪先生。
Boy, your hand is cold, Mr. Peabody.

619
00:34:14,012 --> 00:34:15,513
-谢尔曼？        -怎么了？
- Sherman?       - Yeah?

620
00:34:17,015 --> 00:34:18,016
那不是我的手。
That's not my hand.

621
00:34:24,397 --> 00:34:26,149
那是一只断臂。
That's disarming.

622
00:34:26,191 --> 00:34:29,235
现在，让我们找条路出去吧。
Now, to find a way out of here.

623
00:34:30,362 --> 00:34:31,821
看看周围，谢尔曼。
Look around, Sherman.

624
00:34:31,863 --> 00:34:34,157
这些古墓布满了象形文字…
These tombs are lined with hieroglyphics...

625
00:34:34,199 --> 00:34:38,703
它们被用来在法老们的灵魂转世的途中帮助他们。
designed to assist the pharaohs' souls in their journey to the afterlife.

626
00:34:38,745 --> 00:34:41,873
这些文字也许也可以帮助我们。
And they may assist us as well.

627
00:34:43,875 --> 00:34:47,754
这幅画描述了阿努比斯之神驾驶着拉神的船去冥界。
This depicts the god Anubis sailing the boat of Ra to the underworld.

628
00:34:47,796 --> 00:34:51,383
这意味着拉神的船是我们逃出这里的关键。
It appears the boats of Ra are the key to our escape.

629
00:34:51,424 --> 00:34:53,677
我们必须及时找到它们来阻止婚礼。
We must find them in time to stop the wedding.

630
00:34:53,718 --> 00:34:56,388
呃，如果你问我的话，我们应该让她嫁给那个家伙。
Well, if you ask me, we should let her marry that guy.

631
00:34:56,429 --> 00:34:57,722
他们挺配得上对方的。
They deserve each other.

632
00:34:57,764 --> 00:34:59,057
怎么了，谢尔曼？
What's that, Sherman?

633
00:34:59,099 --> 00:35:00,684
图特？别贫了。
Tut? Give me a break.

634
00:35:00,725 --> 00:35:04,062
秃顶，穿着衬衫，还化妆。
Bald, wears a skirt, and makeup.

635
00:35:04,104 --> 00:35:06,773
按照我的理解，谢尔曼，我认为你在吃醋。
If I didn't know any better, Sherman, I would say you were jealous.

636
00:35:06,815 --> 00:35:08,733
吃醋？吃谁的醋？
Jealous? Of what?

637
00:35:08,775 --> 00:35:10,694
图特对佩妮的喜爱，不是吗？
Tut's affection for Penny, of course.

638
00:35:10,735 --> 00:35:12,153
你以为我喜欢佩妮？
You think I like Penny?

639
00:35:13,780 --> 00:35:15,031
别贫了！
Give me a break!

640
00:35:15,073 --> 00:35:19,869
这不比我想牵她的手，或者去公园 
It's not like I want to hold her hand, or go to the park...

641
00:35:19,911 --> 00:35:22,747
或者看着她梳头发。
or watch her while she's brushing her hair.

642
00:35:25,667 --> 00:35:27,085
或者别的任何事。
Or anything.

643
00:35:33,967 --> 00:35:35,510
快点，谢尔曼。
Quickly, Sherman.

644
00:35:39,639 --> 00:35:41,307
小心点，谢尔曼。
Careful, Sherman.

645
00:35:41,349 --> 00:35:42,934
这是个诱杀装置。
It's a booby trap.

646
00:35:43,935 --> 00:35:46,771
-有什么好笑的？         -你刚刚说“傻瓜”。
- What's so funny?      - You said "booby."

647
00:35:48,857 --> 00:35:51,359
只要踏错一步我们就完了。
One wrong step and we're done for.

648
00:35:53,111 --> 00:35:54,320
“拉神…
"The boat...

649
00:35:54,362 --> 00:35:56,865
“的船直向
"of Ra sails straight...

650
00:35:57,282 --> 00:35:58,408
“白天。
"to day.

651
00:35:58,450 --> 00:36:02,120
“搭上了错误的船…
"Take the wrong boat...

652
00:36:02,162 --> 00:36:03,580
“就会付出代价。
man will pay."

653
00:36:03,621 --> 00:36:04,873
好了，谢尔曼，轮到你了。
All right, Sherman, now it's your turn.

654
00:36:05,165 --> 00:36:07,709
像我完全一样地解开这个谜底。
Do the puzzle exactly as I did.

655
00:36:08,126 --> 00:36:10,670
好好想，一次一格。
Think it through, one step at a time.

656
00:36:15,050 --> 00:36:16,968
拉神的船直向…
The boat of Ra sails straight...

657
00:36:17,010 --> 00:36:18,011
玩。
play.

658
00:36:18,970 --> 00:36:20,180
我的意思是，“还”。
I mean, "pay."

659
00:36:20,221 --> 00:36:21,306
哦，天哪。
Oh, my.

660
00:36:24,809 --> 00:36:26,019
哦哦。
Uh-oh.

661
00:36:28,688 --> 00:36:29,731
快跑！
Run!

662
00:36:35,195 --> 00:36:36,863
拉神的船！
The boats of Ra!

663
00:36:36,905 --> 00:36:38,948
一只船可以带我们离开这里，另一只则会…
One boat is the way out, the other will send us...

664
00:36:38,990 --> 00:36:40,700
带我们陷入黑暗和死亡。
plunging into darkness and certain death.

665
00:36:40,742 --> 00:36:42,202
什么？
What?

666
00:36:42,243 --> 00:36:43,370
谢尔曼，去船上。
Sherman, get in the boat.

667
00:36:43,411 --> 00:36:46,456
当我把这些方块组合起来时，船将会移动得很快。
As soon as I move these blocks together, it's going to move very fast.

668
00:36:46,498 --> 00:36:48,875
-哪一只船，皮博迪先生？         -什么？
- Which boat, Mr. Peabody?      - What?

669
00:36:48,917 --> 00:36:51,628
哪一只船不是“带我们陷入黑暗和死亡”的船？
Which boat is the "not-certain-death-plunge" boat?

670
00:36:51,670 --> 00:36:52,837
那一只！
That one!

671
00:37:06,518 --> 00:37:07,727
我们做到了，谢尔曼！
We did it, Sherman!

672
00:37:07,769 --> 00:37:08,895
谢尔曼？
Sherman?

673
00:37:08,937 --> 00:37:10,730
皮博迪先生！
Mr. Peabody!

674
00:37:10,772 --> 00:37:12,190
你在那里干嘛？
What are you doing over there?

675
00:37:12,232 --> 00:37:14,442
我以为你指的是这艘船！
I thought you pointed to this one!

676
00:37:39,884 --> 00:37:42,053
谢尔曼？谢尔曼？
Sherman? Sherman?

677
00:37:42,095 --> 00:37:43,555
你还好吗？
Are you all right?

678
00:37:44,264 --> 00:37:45,849
我还行。
I'm good.

679
00:37:58,820 --> 00:38:00,697
太阳之神，拉神…
The sun god, Ra...

680
00:38:00,739 --> 00:38:05,410
要求我们开始这场神圣的庆典！
commands us to begin the sacred ceremony!

681
00:38:15,462 --> 00:38:19,090
把刀刃带上前来准备血誓。
Bring forth the blade for the blood oath.

682
00:38:23,261 --> 00:38:28,016
当刀锋在这场神圣的仪式上与血肉相遇…
Where blade meets flesh in this sacred rite...

683
00:38:30,643 --> 00:38:32,062
我们以此贡品…
we pay tribute...

684
00:38:32,103 --> 00:38:34,272
献给太阳之神，拉神！
to the sun god, Ra!

685
00:38:35,023 --> 00:38:36,274
等等！
Wait!

686
00:38:37,942 --> 00:38:39,069
阿努比斯！
Anubis!

687
00:38:39,110 --> 00:38:40,403
死亡之神！
The god of death!

688
00:38:40,445 --> 00:38:42,739
婚礼不可以继续。
The wedding must not continue.

689
00:38:42,781 --> 00:38:44,783
为什么，阿努比斯，为什么？
Why, Anubis, why?

690
00:38:44,824 --> 00:38:47,327
瘟疫，瘟疫！
Plagues. Plagues!

691
00:38:47,660 --> 00:38:49,954
如果这门婚事定下来了…
If this marriage pact is sealed...

692
00:38:49,996 --> 00:38:53,958
我会在这片大地降下难以数计的瘟疫。
I will shower down upon the land uncountable plagues.

693
00:38:54,000 --> 00:38:55,627
靠，又是瘟疫！
Oy, again with the plagues!

694
00:38:55,669 --> 00:38:57,796
我干嘛要搬到埃及来？
Why did I ever move to Egypt?

695
00:38:57,837 --> 00:39:01,091
但是，阿努比斯，太阳之神，拉神，曾宣布…
But, Anubis, the sun god, Ra, has decreed...

696
00:39:01,132 --> 00:39:03,802
这个女孩定要成为这个男孩的王妃。
that this girl is to be the boy-king's wife.

697
00:39:04,177 --> 00:39:05,762
那就有趣了。
That's so funny.

698
00:39:05,804 --> 00:39:09,140
我那天在和拉神聊天时…
I was talking to the sun god, Ra, just the other day...

699
00:39:09,182 --> 00:39:11,851
他跟我说他改主意了。
and he told me he changed his mind.

700
00:39:11,893 --> 00:39:12,936
真的？
Really?

701
00:39:12,977 --> 00:39:17,023
所以我们在冥界都叫他“成天改主意的拉神”。
Old "Flip-Flop Ra," we call him here in the underworld.

702
00:39:17,065 --> 00:39:20,235
但现在太迟了。我们已经付了那么多钱了。
But it's too late. We've already paid for the catering.

703
00:39:21,861 --> 00:39:25,198
太糟了！你们就要失去我对你们的保佑了。
Too bad! You're going to lose your deposit.

704
00:39:27,701 --> 00:39:31,287
再来点烟，谢尔曼。这个阿努比斯之狗诡计起作用了。
More smoke, Sherman. This canine subterfuge is working.

705
00:39:31,329 --> 00:39:32,622
交出那个女孩…
Deliver the girl...

706
00:39:32,664 --> 00:39:35,667
把她放在城门，留她在那里…
to the gates of the city, and leave her there...

707
00:39:35,709 --> 00:39:38,962
让神可以重新得到她。
where the gods will retrieve her forthwith.

708
00:39:39,004 --> 00:39:43,133
只有这样做才可以让这片土地避免瘟疫。
Only in this manner may the plagues upon this land be avoided.

709
00:39:43,174 --> 00:39:45,301
放那个女孩走！
The girl must go!

710
00:39:45,343 --> 00:39:47,012
放那个女孩走！
The girl must go!

711
00:39:47,762 --> 00:39:49,639
阿努比斯发话了！
Anubis has spoken!

712
00:39:49,681 --> 00:39:51,891
把那个女孩带去城门！
Take this girl to the gates!

713
00:39:58,523 --> 00:40:01,192
阿努比斯，你听起来不太好。
Anubis, you sound unwell.

714
00:40:01,234 --> 00:40:03,862
呃，我最近总觉得人有点不舒服…
Well, I have been feeling a little under the weather...

715
00:40:03,903 --> 00:40:06,531
但我现在感觉好多了。
but I'm feeling much better now.

716
00:40:07,240 --> 00:40:08,450
谢谢。
Thank you.

717
00:40:19,711 --> 00:40:21,588
佩妮，谢尔曼，快点！
Penny, Sherman, quickly.

718
00:40:21,629 --> 00:40:22,714
过来，佩妮。
Come on, Penny.

719
00:40:22,756 --> 00:40:23,923
谢尔曼！
Sherman!

720
00:40:29,721 --> 00:40:31,222
逃跑的新娘！
Runaway bride!

721
00:40:31,264 --> 00:40:32,807
把他们拦下，你们这些蠢货！
Stop them, you fools!

722
00:40:52,786 --> 00:40:54,913
佩妮，谢尔曼，爬上去。
Penny, Sherman, climb aboard.

723
00:41:05,256 --> 00:41:07,258
他们就要跑掉了！
They're getting away!

724
00:41:23,858 --> 00:41:25,610
我捡到了。
I got it.

725
00:41:27,570 --> 00:41:28,613
我们逃出来了。
We made it.

726
00:41:28,655 --> 00:41:30,615
-我们接下来要去哪，皮博迪先生？           -回家。
- Where do we go next, Mr. Peabody?       - Home.

727
00:41:30,657 --> 00:41:32,409
我们一定要在佩妮的父母发现她失踪前…
We've got to get back to the dinner party...

728
00:41:32,450 --> 00:41:34,452
回到派对上。
before Penny's parents realize she's missing.

729
00:41:34,494 --> 00:41:36,955
我们不需要提到整个…
We don't have to mention the whole...

730
00:41:36,996 --> 00:41:38,915
图特王的婚事什么的，对不？
King Tut wedding thing, right?

731
00:41:38,957 --> 00:41:40,250
是的。
Certainly not.

732
00:41:40,291 --> 00:41:43,962
无论如何，就我看来，古埃及的人都太早结婚了。
Anyway, as far as I'm concerned, they get married too young in Ancient Egypt.

733
00:41:44,004 --> 00:41:46,881
或者我可能只是老“吉萨”。
Or, perhaps, I'm just some old "Giza."

734
00:41:51,136 --> 00:41:52,178
警告。
<i>Warning.</i>

735
00:41:52,679 --> 00:41:54,931
WABAC能量供应不足。
<i>WABAC power supply insufficient.</i>

736
00:41:54,973 --> 00:41:57,517
正在充电。警告。
<i>Charge now. Warning.</i>

737
00:41:57,559 --> 00:41:59,269
怎么了，皮博迪先生？
What's the matter, Mr. Peabody?

738
00:41:59,310 --> 00:42:02,147
频繁地撕开宇宙裂缝榨干了我们的能源供应。
All this zipping about the cosmos has drained our power supply.

739
00:42:02,188 --> 00:42:04,315
我们将不得不进行计划外的停止。
We're going to have to make an unscheduled stop.

740
00:42:04,607 --> 00:42:05,775
走运的是…
As luck would have it...

741
00:42:05,817 --> 00:42:08,018
我们刚刚好有足够的能源使我们到达文艺复兴时期。
we have just enough power to make it to the Renaissance.

742
00:42:20,999 --> 00:42:24,627
我甚至没法区别出我的左右脑了！
I can't even tell my left brain from my right anymore!

743
00:42:24,669 --> 00:42:26,796
我已经告诉你多少次了，蒙娜丽莎？
How many times I got to tell you, Mona Lisa?

744
00:42:26,838 --> 00:42:27,839
蒙娜丽莎？
Mona Lisa?

745
00:42:27,881 --> 00:42:30,133
如果你不笑的话…
I can't paint the picture...

746
00:42:30,175 --> 00:42:32,218
我就没法画！
until you smile!

747
00:42:32,260 --> 00:42:35,972
莱昂纳多，告诉我一件值得让我微笑的事。
Leonardo, tell me one thing I have to smile about.

748
00:42:36,014 --> 00:42:37,891
阳光，意大利面。
The sunshine, the pasta.

749
00:42:37,932 --> 00:42:41,895
所有这些让意大利成为游览景点的都值得你微笑！
All the things that make Italy such a popular tourist destination!

750
00:42:41,936 --> 00:42:44,856
但这些东西我都没见过，莱昂纳多！
But I have not seen any of them, Leonardo!

751
00:42:44,898 --> 00:42:48,193
因为我整天都坐在我的abbondanza上！
Because I'm sitting here all day on my <i>abbondanza!</i>

752
00:42:49,027 --> 00:42:51,863
我认为那个词在意大利语里不是“椅子”的意思。
I don't think that means "chair" in Italian.

753
00:42:52,697 --> 00:42:55,158
皮博迪，我的老朋友。
Peabody, my old friend.

754
00:42:55,200 --> 00:42:57,744
多么欢迎的来扰！
What a welcome interruption!

755
00:42:57,786 --> 00:43:01,498
相信我，这个女的快让我变傻了。
Believe you me, this woman is making me nuts.

756
00:43:01,539 --> 00:43:03,249
那么，近来如何？
So, how you been?

757
00:43:03,291 --> 00:43:05,210
真高兴见到你。你想做什么？
Good to see you. What do you want?

758
00:43:05,251 --> 00:43:09,047
我们非常急着回家，但是WABAC需要一个跃进式启动…
We're in a desperate hurry to get home, but the WABAC needs a jump start...

759
00:43:09,089 --> 00:43:13,843
然后我们就想，有谁可以比莱昂纳多·达·芬奇做得更好帮我们回家？
and we thought, who better than Leonardo da Vinci to help us on our way?

760
00:43:13,885 --> 00:43:18,932
皮博迪，我很愿意帮助你，但是你来的真不是时候。
Peabody, I would love to help you, but you come at a very bad time.

761
00:43:18,973 --> 00:43:22,060
我不知道要怎么应付这个疯女人。
I don't know what I'm going to do with this crazy woman.

762
00:43:23,603 --> 00:43:25,939
-知道我什么意思了吧？         -有什么难题吗？
- You see what I mean?        - What seems to be the problem?

763
00:43:25,980 --> 00:43:27,440
“有什么麻烦吗？”
"What is the problem?"

764
00:43:27,482 --> 00:43:30,193
这幅画我都快画完了，但是她就是不肯笑。
I am halfway done with the painting, she won't even smile.

765
00:43:30,235 --> 00:43:33,113
好的。我笑给你看。
Fine. I smile.

766
00:43:35,573 --> 00:43:38,034
不！那个笑容是假的！
No! That's a fake smile!

767
00:43:38,076 --> 00:43:39,536
每个人都看得出来！
Everybody knows that!

768
00:43:39,577 --> 00:43:41,955
你为什么不真的笑出来？
Why don't you make it a real smile?

769
00:43:41,996 --> 00:43:43,581
你干嘛不说些有趣的东西？
Why don't you say something funny?

770
00:43:43,623 --> 00:43:45,208
我只顾画画。
I paint the paintings.

771
00:43:45,250 --> 00:43:47,210
我会造机器。
I make the machines.

772
00:43:47,252 --> 00:43:50,130
我不会讲笑话！
I don't tell the jokes!

773
00:43:50,171 --> 00:43:52,882
也许，我可以帮到你。你瞧…
Perhaps, I can be of assistance. You see...

774
00:43:52,924 --> 00:43:55,093
幽默并不与科学定律互相排斥。
humor is not immune to the laws of science.

775
00:43:55,135 --> 00:43:58,930
运用算法，我们就可以推断出什么是广义上的“有趣”…
Using algorithms, we can extrapolate what is universally considered "funny"...

776
00:43:58,972 --> 00:44:03,268
接着就用科学的方法准确写出可以制造笑声的方程式。
thus producing a formula that is scientifically certain to cause laughter.

777
00:44:03,685 --> 00:44:06,271
举一个恰当的例子，屁股着地的摔倒。
Case in point, the pratfall.

778
00:44:12,110 --> 00:44:14,320
每个人都被我逗笑了么？
Is everyone amused?

779
00:44:17,615 --> 00:44:19,325
数据看起来是如此清楚。
The data was so clear.

780
00:44:19,367 --> 00:44:20,785
别担心，皮博迪先生。
Don't worry, Mr. Peabody.

781
00:44:20,827 --> 00:44:22,203
-让我来！        -谢尔曼…
- I got it!      - Sherman...

782
00:44:37,802 --> 00:44:39,262
保持住那个微笑！
Hold that smile!

783
00:44:39,304 --> 00:44:41,306
就是那样！别动！别动！
Hold it right there! No move! No move!

784
00:44:49,356 --> 00:44:52,192
莱昂，如果我的计算式正确的话…
Well, Leo, if my calculations are correct...

785
00:44:52,233 --> 00:44:54,986
我们的机器应该要产生足够的离心力…
this machine of ours should generate enough centrifugal force...

786
00:44:55,028 --> 00:44:56,363
来带我们回家。
to send us home.

787
00:44:56,404 --> 00:44:58,948
我这有一块零件需要用锤子锤好。
I got one last piece I gotta pound in place.

788
00:44:58,990 --> 00:45:02,285
谢尔曼，为什么不把那只锤子拿给达芬奇先生呢？
Sherman, why don't you fetch the hammer for Mr. Da Vinci?

789
00:45:02,327 --> 00:45:04,162
好的，皮博迪先生。
Okay, Mr. Peabody.

790
00:45:08,833 --> 00:45:10,001
皮博迪先生！
Mr. Peabody!

791
00:45:10,043 --> 00:45:11,294
做得好，谢尔曼。
Well done, Sherman.

792
00:45:11,336 --> 00:45:12,462
但是，皮博迪先生！
But, Mr. Peabody!

793
00:45:12,504 --> 00:45:13,838
你真会帮忙。
Very helpful.

794
00:45:28,353 --> 00:45:29,521
谢尔曼！
Sherman!

795
00:45:30,021 --> 00:45:31,523
是的，皮博迪先生？
Yes, Mr. Peabody?

796
00:45:32,232 --> 00:45:33,441
那支锤子。
The hammer.

797
00:45:33,942 --> 00:45:35,110
达芬奇。
Da Vinci.

798
00:45:36,027 --> 00:45:37,862
好的，皮博迪先生。
Okay, Mr. Peabody.

799
00:45:41,533 --> 00:45:43,076
我拿来给你了，达芬奇先生。
Here you go, Mr. Da Vinci.

800
00:45:43,118 --> 00:45:44,327
你还需要帮忙吗？
Do you need any help?

801
00:45:44,369 --> 00:45:46,329
不，不。那样就好。
No, no. That's quite all right.

802
00:45:46,371 --> 00:45:47,872
谢谢。
Thank you.

803
00:45:48,623 --> 00:45:49,624
谢尔曼。
Sherman.

804
00:45:50,083 --> 00:45:52,377
咋们一起看探险。
Let's go. Let's go explore.

805
00:45:53,044 --> 00:45:57,382
呃，我应该在这儿和皮博迪先生一起干活的。
Well, I'm supposed to be having father-son time with Mr. Peabody.

806
00:45:57,424 --> 00:45:59,092
你就不更想和我一起玩？
Wouldn't you rather have fun with me?

807
00:46:00,635 --> 00:46:01,720
好吧。
Okay.

808
00:46:01,761 --> 00:46:02,929
谢尔曼…
Sherman...

809
00:46:02,971 --> 00:46:04,180
你想去哪里？
where are you going?

810
00:46:04,222 --> 00:46:05,432
探险。
Exploring.

811
00:46:05,473 --> 00:46:06,725
但我们需要你的帮助。
But we need your help.

812
00:46:06,766 --> 00:46:09,394
不，我们不需要！我的意思是，我们搞得掂。
No, we don't! I mean, we can manage.

813
00:46:09,436 --> 00:46:10,562
怎样都行。
Somehow.

814
00:46:11,146 --> 00:46:12,564
他是个小男孩，皮博迪。
He's a boy, Peabody.

815
00:46:12,605 --> 00:46:15,358
让他玩去吧。让他走。
Let him have his fun. Let him go.

816
00:46:15,400 --> 00:46:17,068
谢谢，皮博迪先生！
Thanks, Mr. Peabody!

817
00:46:20,655 --> 00:46:22,907
他在长大，皮博迪。
He's growing up, Peabody.

818
00:46:22,949 --> 00:46:25,994
就像一只将要离开巢穴的小鸟。
Like a baby bird leaving the nest.

819
00:46:26,244 --> 00:46:28,580
那不美好吗？
Isn't it wonderful?

820
00:46:35,587 --> 00:46:37,756
这儿就像博物馆。
It's like a museum.

821
00:46:38,590 --> 00:46:41,092
这儿就像玩具店。
It's like a toy store.

822
00:46:45,930 --> 00:46:47,599
哇哦。
Wow.

823
00:46:51,436 --> 00:46:52,729
看看这个。
Check this out.

824
00:46:52,771 --> 00:46:55,398
这是世界最大的飞机模型。
It's the world's biggest model airplane.

825
00:46:55,440 --> 00:46:58,234
这不是飞机模型，佩妮。这是个飞机原型。
It's not a model, Penny. It's a prototype.

826
00:46:58,276 --> 00:47:01,321
我们也许不应该去碰它。
And we should probably just leave that alone.

827
00:47:01,363 --> 00:47:02,405
好的。
Okay.

828
00:47:02,447 --> 00:47:04,657
如果我们可以驾驶它的话那不是很酷吗？
But wouldn't it be cool if we could fly it?

829
00:47:04,699 --> 00:47:06,826
我认为皮博士先生不会喜欢这样的。
I don't think Mr. Peabody would like that.

830
00:47:06,868 --> 00:47:09,079
可是，皮博迪先生不在这里。
Well, Mr. Peabody isn't here.

831
00:47:09,120 --> 00:47:10,789
告诉我怎么让它飞起来就好了。
Just tell me how it works.

832
00:47:10,830 --> 00:47:12,040
求你了。
Please?

833
00:47:12,290 --> 00:47:13,500
知道一下就好。
For learning.

834
00:47:14,167 --> 00:47:15,627
好吧。
Okay.

835
00:47:16,127 --> 00:47:19,422
这个像弓弩的装置提供了飞行器起飞的推力。
The thrust comes from this kind of crossbow doohickey here.

836
00:47:19,464 --> 00:47:23,593
接着飞行器沿着这个轨道发射出去直到风把机翼托起来。
Then it shoots along the track until the wind catches the wings.

837
00:47:23,635 --> 00:47:25,512
可是要怎样发射呢？
But how does it go?

838
00:47:25,553 --> 00:47:27,097
应该怎么起飞？
How do you take off?

839
00:47:27,138 --> 00:47:29,224
你只要拉那个把手就好了。
You just pull down that lever.

840
00:47:30,475 --> 00:47:31,851
这支吗？
This one?

841
00:47:31,893 --> 00:47:33,019
哦天哪。
Oh, boy.

842
00:47:41,695 --> 00:47:43,446
这太疯狂了！
This is crazy!

843
00:47:43,488 --> 00:47:45,865
不，这不疯狂，谢尔曼！这很好玩！
No, it's not Sherman. It's fun!

844
00:47:45,907 --> 00:47:47,325
我们要死在这里了！
We're gonna die!

845
00:47:47,367 --> 00:47:50,161
别像个胆小鬼似的，快嗨起来吧！
Stop being such a party pooper and enjoy it!

846
00:47:56,835 --> 00:47:59,796
没什么事比优雅的方程式…
Nothing is as beautiful as an elegant equation...

847
00:47:59,838 --> 00:48:02,632
转化为完美的工程那样美妙了。
translated into perfect engineering.

848
00:48:02,674 --> 00:48:04,801
为什么小孩就不能这样简单？
Why can't children be so simple?

849
00:48:04,843 --> 00:48:07,971
因为小孩不是机器，谢尔曼。
Because children are not machines, Peabody.

850
00:48:08,013 --> 00:48:11,349
相信我，我试过造一个小孩。
Believe me, I tried to build one.

851
00:48:11,391 --> 00:48:13,518
那太可怕了。
It was creepy.

852
00:48:15,937 --> 00:48:17,689
给你，谢尔曼！你来控制。
Here, Sherman! You fly it!

853
00:48:17,731 --> 00:48:19,149
但我不想控制！
But I don't want to fly!

854
00:48:19,190 --> 00:48:21,151
你当然想。这很有趣的！
Sure you do. It'll be fun!

855
00:48:21,192 --> 00:48:23,903
不，说真的，佩妮，我真的不想！
No, seriously, Penny, I don't want to!

856
00:48:23,945 --> 00:48:25,822
我要放手了。一…
I'm letting go. One...

857
00:48:25,864 --> 00:48:26,990
别放手！
Don't let go!

858
00:48:27,032 --> 00:48:28,074
二…
Two...

859
00:48:28,116 --> 00:48:29,617
-不！         -三！
- No!         - Three!

860
00:48:32,871 --> 00:48:34,039
佩妮，快让它飞起来！
Penny, fly the plane!

861
00:48:34,539 --> 00:48:35,749
不，谢尔曼！
No, Sherman!

862
00:48:35,790 --> 00:48:38,084
-你必须救我们！                      -但我做不到！
- You're going to have to save us!   - But I can't do it!

863
00:48:38,626 --> 00:48:41,588
我是认真的，佩妮。我不知道怎么飞！
I'm serious, Penny. I don't know how to fly!

864
00:48:41,629 --> 00:48:43,506
你可以的！我知道你一定行的！
You can do it! I know you can!

865
00:48:43,548 --> 00:48:44,716
来吧，谢尔曼。
Come on, Sherman.

866
00:48:44,758 --> 00:48:45,759
飞起来！
Fly!

867
00:49:11,910 --> 00:49:14,037
看见了吧？你做到了，谢尔曼。
See? You got this, Sherman.

868
00:49:14,079 --> 00:49:16,790
你是对的。我做到了。
You're right. I have got this.

869
00:49:25,423 --> 00:49:26,966
又是达芬奇在飞！
Da Vinci's at it again!

870
00:49:27,008 --> 00:49:28,718
你见过他造的那个孩子吗？
You ever see that child he made?

871
00:49:28,760 --> 00:49:30,220
太惊悚了。
So creepy.

872
00:49:30,261 --> 00:49:31,805
爸爸。妈妈。
Papa. Mama.

873
00:49:33,014 --> 00:49:34,474
爸爸。妈妈。
Papa. Mama.

874
00:50:01,459 --> 00:50:03,003
我这上面干完了，莱昂纳多。
All done up here, Leonardo.

875
00:50:03,044 --> 00:50:05,338
我这下面也干完了。
And I am all done down here.

876
00:50:05,380 --> 00:50:07,257
这太美了，不是吗？
It is beautiful, isn't it?

877
00:50:07,298 --> 00:50:11,594
每个零件都在自身的位置准确地做它该做的事。
Every piece in its place doing precisely what it's supposed to do.

878
00:50:11,636 --> 00:50:13,179
看，皮博迪！
Look, Peabody!

879
00:50:13,221 --> 00:50:15,265
那是我的飞行…
It's my flying mach...

880
00:50:15,306 --> 00:50:16,641
我的飞行器！
My flying machine?

881
00:50:16,891 --> 00:50:17,934
谢尔曼。
Sherman.

882
00:50:17,976 --> 00:50:19,102
谢尔曼？
Sherman?

883
00:50:19,144 --> 00:50:21,521
谢尔曼，你在上面干嘛？
Sherman, what are you doing up there?

884
00:50:21,563 --> 00:50:23,106
我在飞！
I'm flying!

885
00:50:23,148 --> 00:50:25,817
但是，谢尔曼，你不知道怎样飞！
But, Sherman, you don't know how to fly!

886
00:50:25,859 --> 00:50:26,943
我不知道？
I don't?

887
00:50:26,985 --> 00:50:27,986
是的！
No!

888
00:50:34,492 --> 00:50:35,618
快转弯！
Turn!

889
00:50:35,660 --> 00:50:36,703
快转弯，谢尔曼！
Turn, Sherman!

890
00:50:36,745 --> 00:50:37,787
倾斜！
Lean!

891
00:50:37,829 --> 00:50:38,872
倾斜！
Lean!

892
00:50:51,843 --> 00:50:52,969
谢尔曼？
Sherman?

893
00:50:53,011 --> 00:50:55,347
谢尔曼！你还好吗？
Sherman! Are you okay?

894
00:50:55,388 --> 00:50:58,058
刚才那个太赞了！
That was pretty fantastic!

895
00:50:59,184 --> 00:51:01,394
难以置信！
I can't believe it!

896
00:51:02,354 --> 00:51:04,606
我的飞行器！它飞起来了！
My flying machine! It's work!

897
00:51:05,690 --> 00:51:09,319
谢尔曼！你是第一个飞起来的人！
Sherman! You are the first flying man!

898
00:51:09,361 --> 00:51:11,363
你应该很自豪，皮博迪。
You should be very proud, Peabody.

899
00:51:11,404 --> 00:51:13,198
非常，非常自豪！
Very, very proud!

900
00:51:13,239 --> 00:51:15,367
我可没有觉得“自豪”。
"Proud" doesn't begin to describe it.

901
00:51:17,202 --> 00:51:19,704
莱昂纳多，请你发动那个装置好吗？
Leonardo, will you please fire up the mechanism?

902
00:51:38,390 --> 00:51:40,600
爸爸。妈妈。
Papa. Mama.

903
00:51:40,642 --> 00:51:42,102
爸爸。妈妈。
Papa. Mama.

904
00:51:42,143 --> 00:51:43,937
蒙娜！
Mona!

905
00:51:45,605 --> 00:51:46,648
爸爸。妈妈。
Papa. Mama.

906
00:51:46,690 --> 00:51:47,691
那个孩子！
The kid!

907
00:52:14,175 --> 00:52:16,886
很抱歉我弄坏了那个飞行器，皮博迪先生。
I'm sorry I broke the plane, Mr. Peabody.

908
00:52:16,928 --> 00:52:19,597
是的，你应该觉得抱歉。你甚至可能会摔死。
Well, you should be. You could have been killed.

909
00:52:19,639 --> 00:52:21,099
你在说什么？
What are you talking about?

910
00:52:21,141 --> 00:52:23,935
谢尔曼刚刚在开飞机。他太棒了！
Sherman flew a plane. He was amazing!

911
00:52:23,977 --> 00:52:27,522
谢尔曼毁掉了一件无价的历史文物。
Sherman destroyed a priceless historical artifact.

912
00:52:27,564 --> 00:52:29,858
我才不管那是什么。你应该觉得高兴。
Whatever. You should be happy.

913
00:52:29,899 --> 00:52:32,569
毕竟那说明了谢尔曼不是一个一无是处的失败者。
It turns out Sherman is not a complete and total loser, after all.

914
00:52:32,610 --> 00:52:33,862
是的，皮博迪先生。
Yeah, Mr. Peabody.

915
00:52:33,903 --> 00:52:36,573
毕竟那说明了我不是一个一无是处的失败者。
It turns out I'm not a complete and total loser, after all.

916
00:52:38,324 --> 00:52:39,409
彼得逊女士…
Ms. Peterson...

917
00:52:39,451 --> 00:52:42,078
别再把我的孩子教成一个小混混。
stop turning my son into a hooligan.

918
00:52:42,120 --> 00:52:43,538
他是个小混混又不是我的错。
It's not my fault he's a hooligan.

919
00:52:43,580 --> 00:52:46,207
就是，我是个小混混又不是她的错。
Yeah, it's not her fault I'm a hooligan.

920
00:52:46,249 --> 00:52:47,751
可那显然也不是我的错！
Well, it's certainly not my fault!

921
00:52:47,792 --> 00:52:50,879
我花了七年时间培养了谢尔曼良好的判断力。
I've spent the last seven years teaching Sherman good judgment.

922
00:52:50,920 --> 00:52:52,005
如果你真是个好家长…
If you're such a great parent...

923
00:52:52,047 --> 00:52:54,632
那为什么古宁恩女士要把他从你身边带走？
why is Ms. Grunion trying to take Sherman away from you?

924
00:52:57,677 --> 00:52:59,304
那是真的吗？
Is that true?

925
00:52:59,346 --> 00:53:01,556
有人要把我从你身边带走？
Is someone gonna take me away from you?

926
00:53:01,598 --> 00:53:04,059
不，谢尔曼，我是不会让它发生的。
No, Sherman, I'll never let that happen.

927
00:53:04,100 --> 00:53:05,810
请相信我。
You just need to trust me.

928
00:53:05,852 --> 00:53:08,188
哦，天啊，黑洞！
Oh, dear, a black hole!

929
00:53:13,943 --> 00:53:15,403
发生了什么事？
What's happening?

930
00:53:15,445 --> 00:53:16,821
如果我不能把我们拉出这里…
If I can't pull us out of here...

931
00:53:16,863 --> 00:53:19,824
我们就会在黑洞表面被压成碎片。
we're going to be smashed to smithereens on the event horizon.

932
00:53:24,913 --> 00:53:27,624
这台机器已经没有足够的动力来抵抗这么强大的引力了！
There's not enough power to resist the gravitational pull!

933
00:53:28,041 --> 00:53:30,752
我要启动倒退助推器来帮我们转向。
I've got to divert everything to the reverse thrusters.

934
00:53:30,794 --> 00:53:31,920
你为什么不告诉我？
Why didn't you tell me?

935
00:53:31,961 --> 00:53:33,004
告诉你什么？
Tell you what?

936
00:53:33,046 --> 00:53:36,091
为什么不告诉我古宁恩夫人要把我从你身边带走？
Why didn't you tell me Ms. Grunion was trying to take me away from you?

937
00:53:36,424 --> 00:53:38,301
那不是你该担心的事情。
It's not your job to worry about these things.

938
00:53:38,343 --> 00:53:40,011
你只是认为我没法解决这件事。
You just didn't think I could handle it.

939
00:53:40,053 --> 00:53:42,263
我们等会再来讨论这个问题。现在，坐下。
We'll discuss it later. Now, sit down.

940
00:53:42,305 --> 00:53:44,307
我现在就想讨论这个问题！
I don't want to discuss it later!

941
00:53:44,349 --> 00:53:45,809
谢尔曼，坐下！
Sherman, sit!

942
00:53:45,850 --> 00:53:47,894
你不可以和我这样说话。
You can't talk to me like that.

943
00:53:47,936 --> 00:53:50,689
-我才不是一只狗。    -你说什么？
- I'm not a dog.     - What did you say?

944
00:53:50,730 --> 00:53:53,149
我说，我才不是一只狗！
I said, I'm not a dog!

945
00:53:53,608 --> 00:53:55,944
你说得没错，谢尔曼，你不是。
You're right, Sherman, you're not.

946
00:53:55,985 --> 00:53:58,279
你只是个非常坏的男孩！
You're just a very bad boy!

947
00:53:58,697 --> 00:54:00,782
倒计时，10…
<i>T-minus 10...</i>

948
00:54:00,824 --> 00:54:02,867
九，八…
<i>Nine, eight...</i>

949
00:54:02,909 --> 00:54:03,993
七…
<i>Seven...</i>

950
00:54:04,035 --> 00:54:05,036
六…
<i>Six...</i>

951
00:54:05,078 --> 00:54:06,329
五…
<i>Five...</i>

952
00:54:06,371 --> 00:54:08,164
四，三…
<i>Four, three...</i>

953
00:54:08,707 --> 00:54:09,833
二…
<i>Two...</i>

954
00:54:09,874 --> 00:54:10,959
一。
<i>One.</i>

955
00:54:25,432 --> 00:54:26,516
谢尔曼？
Sherman?

956
00:54:27,017 --> 00:54:28,351
佩妮？
Penny?

957
00:54:28,393 --> 00:54:30,145
谢尔曼，你还好吗？
Sherman, are you okay?

958
00:54:33,481 --> 00:54:34,941
谢尔曼？
Sherman?

959
00:54:42,365 --> 00:54:44,159
他走了。
He's gone.

960
00:54:44,200 --> 00:54:46,077
我们在哪儿？
Where are we, anyway?

961
00:54:47,412 --> 00:54:48,747
哦，不。
Oh, no.

962
00:54:49,497 --> 00:54:52,208
我们在历史上最残忍的冲突事件之一的边缘…
We're on the brink of one of history's most ferocious conflicts...

963
00:55:07,974 --> 00:55:09,309
送快递的。
Delivery.

964
00:55:17,025 --> 00:55:19,527
现在觉得如何，希腊英雄？
How are we doing, heroes of Greece?

965
00:55:19,569 --> 00:55:20,945
觉得好吗？
Feeling good?

966
00:55:20,987 --> 00:55:22,822
觉得无所不能？
Feeling strong?

967
00:55:23,990 --> 00:55:25,700
好的，现在来热热身子！
Okay, let's get warmed up!

968
00:55:25,742 --> 00:55:27,535
我们并不想从那里面抢点什么东西出来。
We don't want to pull something out there.

969
00:55:27,577 --> 00:55:29,537
想一想阿基里斯的下场。
Remember what happened to Achilles.

970
00:55:29,579 --> 00:55:31,539
他那脚后跟的事。
That whole thing with his heel.

971
00:55:33,458 --> 00:55:34,834
看起来很棒，狄俄墨德斯（希腊著名的大英雄，阿尔戈斯的国王）。
Looking good, Diomedes.

972
00:55:35,835 --> 00:55:37,796
墨涅拉俄斯（斯巴达之王），好样的！
Menelaus, my man!

973
00:55:37,837 --> 00:55:39,172
好样的。
My man.

974
00:55:39,214 --> 00:55:41,591
你准备好要上战场了吗，谢尔曼纳斯？
Are you ready to get on the field, Shermanus?

975
00:55:41,633 --> 00:55:43,885
是的，阿加门农先生（希腊军统帅）。
Sure thing, Mr. Agamemnon.

976
00:55:45,220 --> 00:55:46,262
真可爱。
That's cute.

977
00:55:51,393 --> 00:55:54,396
奥德修斯（曾指挥特洛伊战争），你带来了什么新消息？
Odysseus, what news do you bring?

978
00:55:54,938 --> 00:55:56,815
有人给我们送来了这个。
Someone left this for us.

979
00:55:56,856 --> 00:55:58,233
一个礼物。真好。
A present. Nice.

980
00:55:58,274 --> 00:56:00,527
看起来就像我们的木马一样。
It looks just like our horse.

981
00:56:01,736 --> 00:56:03,405
要我带进来吗？
Should I bring it inside?

982
00:56:04,781 --> 00:56:06,116
不然的话就太粗鲁了。
It would be rude not to.

983
00:56:11,496 --> 00:56:13,331
我可没看见那只狗！
I did not see that coming!

984
00:56:14,541 --> 00:56:17,168
老天啊，这什么味？
Jeez Louise, what is that smell?

985
00:56:20,005 --> 00:56:21,464
这是胜利的味道！
That is the smell of victory.

986
00:56:21,506 --> 00:56:23,925
耶！胜利！
Yeah! Victory!

987
00:56:23,967 --> 00:56:26,845
大家好，雅典，斯巴达，底比斯的壮士们。
Greetings, men of Athens, Sparta and Thebes.

988
00:56:26,886 --> 00:56:28,263
皮博迪在此。
Peabody, here.

989
00:56:28,304 --> 00:56:30,015
我是为谢尔曼而来。
I've come for Sherman.

990
00:56:30,056 --> 00:56:32,017
-你认识这个家伙吗？        -我曾认为我认识…
- Do you know this guy?    - I thought I did...

991
00:56:32,058 --> 00:56:33,643
但现在我不太肯定。
but now I'm not so sure.

992
00:56:33,685 --> 00:56:35,812
那么他就是个间谍！杀了他！
Then he must be a spy. Kill him!

993
00:56:37,439 --> 00:56:38,523
不！不！
No! No!

994
00:56:38,565 --> 00:56:40,984
他是我爸。
He's my dad.

995
00:56:41,026 --> 00:56:42,402
你爸？
Your dad?

996
00:56:42,444 --> 00:56:44,487
他们父子是收养关系。
It's an adoptive relationship.

997
00:56:46,781 --> 00:56:49,868
谢谢你这么照顾我的孩子，阿加门农先生…
Thank you for taking such good care of my son, Agamemnon...

998
00:56:49,909 --> 00:56:52,412
但现在他应该回家了。
but it's time for him to come home.

999
00:56:52,454 --> 00:56:55,248
对不起，皮博迪先生，我已经加入了希腊军队。
Sorry, Mr. Peabody, I've joined the Greek army.

1000
00:56:55,290 --> 00:56:56,708
谢尔曼已经是我们中的一员了。
Shermanus is one of us now.

1001
00:56:56,750 --> 00:56:58,001
-他是我们的兄弟。    -我是他的兄弟。
- He's a brother.    - I'm his brother.

1002
00:56:58,043 --> 00:56:59,085
他是我儿子。
He's my son.

1003
00:56:59,127 --> 00:57:00,527
-他起了誓。           -我了起誓。
- He took an oath.    - I took an oath.

1004
00:57:00,545 --> 00:57:01,796
他才七岁！
He's seven!

1005
00:57:01,838 --> 00:57:03,340
加半年！
And a half!

1006
00:57:03,673 --> 00:57:07,010
所有的孩子应该向他们的父亲证明自己。
All sons must prove themselves to their fathers.

1007
00:57:07,052 --> 00:57:08,136
今天…
Today...

1008
00:57:08,178 --> 00:57:12,349
谢尔曼纳斯将在战场上证明自己。
Shermanus will prove himself on the field of battle.

1009
00:57:12,390 --> 00:57:13,600
但他还是个孩子。
But he's only a child.

1010
00:57:13,641 --> 00:57:16,811
你爸也许认为你还没准备好成为一个男人，谢尔曼纳斯…
Your dad may not think you're ready to become a man, Shermanus...

1011
00:57:16,853 --> 00:57:18,021
但我们都这么认为。
but we do.

1012
00:57:18,063 --> 00:57:20,190
-就是！           -是的，皮博迪先生。
- Yeah!           - Yeah, Mr. Peabody.

1013
00:57:20,231 --> 00:57:22,150
现在我就来给你看看我可以对付的事情。
Now, I'll show you what I can handle.

1014
00:57:22,192 --> 00:57:24,652
事实上，有很多英雄都有类似的烦恼。
FYI, a lot of heroes have father issues.

1015
00:57:24,694 --> 00:57:26,237
我的老爸是个弥诺陶洛斯（人身牛头怪物）。
My old man is a minotaur.

1016
00:57:26,279 --> 00:57:29,532
半人，半牛，大家议论纷纷。
Half man, half bull, all judgment.

1017
00:57:29,574 --> 00:57:31,826
阿贾克斯，在这儿，世界上最强壮的人…
Ajax, here, strongest guy in the world...

1018
00:57:31,868 --> 00:57:35,538
但他的父亲对他真实的梦想是成为歌唱家这件事一直无法接受。
but his father never accepted that his real dream was to sing.

1019
00:57:35,580 --> 00:57:37,457
我想加入希腊合唱团。
I wanted to be in the Greek chorus.

1020
00:57:37,499 --> 00:57:39,668
哦对了，还有俄狄浦斯…
Yeah, and don't even get me started about Oedipus.

1021
00:57:39,709 --> 00:57:43,630
这么说吧，你会一点都不想去他家度假的。
Let's just say that you do not want to be at his house over the holidays.

1022
00:57:43,672 --> 00:57:44,881
这很尴尬。
It's awkward.

1023
00:57:45,465 --> 00:57:47,300
谢尔曼，我觉得你应该好好想想。
Sherman, I'm concerned you haven't thought this through.

1024
00:57:47,342 --> 00:57:50,595
这是战争。你知道那将会发生什么吗？
This is war. Do you realize what's about to happen?

1025
00:57:50,887 --> 00:57:52,472
我来告诉你会发生什么。
I'll tell you what's gonna happen.

1026
00:57:52,514 --> 00:57:54,849
我们会毁掉他们的家园！
We're gonna destroy their houses!

1027
00:57:54,891 --> 00:57:56,351
推倒他们的神庙！
Pull down their temples!

1028
00:57:56,393 --> 00:57:59,437
用特洛伊人的鲜血让城市里的街道…
And make the streets of the city run red...

1029
00:57:59,771 --> 00:58:01,731
染成红色！
with Trojan blood!

1030
00:58:01,773 --> 00:58:02,857
太棒了！
Yeah!

1031
00:58:03,274 --> 00:58:07,487
血！血！血！
Blood! Blood! Blood!

1032
00:58:16,621 --> 00:58:18,456
我数三下！一！
Zeus on three! One!

1033
00:58:18,498 --> 00:58:21,292
谢尔曼，我绝对禁止你参加特洛伊战争。
Sherman, I absolutely forbid you to fight in the Trojan War.

1034
00:58:21,334 --> 00:58:24,254
这不公平！我的所有朋友都将参加。
It's not fair! All my friends are fighting in the Trojan War.

1035
00:58:24,295 --> 00:58:26,006
-二！          -谢尔曼，这很危险。
- Two!         - Sherman, it's dangerous.

1036
00:58:26,047 --> 00:58:27,215
我戴着头盔。
I'm wearing a helmet.

1037
00:58:27,257 --> 00:58:28,591
-三！        -你别走！
- Three!     - You're not going!

1038
00:58:28,633 --> 00:58:29,843
我偏要走。
Yes, I am.

1039
00:58:29,884 --> 00:58:31,594
上啊！
Zeus!

1040
00:58:36,891 --> 00:58:40,145
吃我一剑，你们这些特洛伊狗！
Eat my bronze, you Trojan dogs!

1041
00:58:42,188 --> 00:58:44,315
吃我一剑，你们这些特洛伊狗！
Eat my bronze, you Trojan dog!

1042
00:58:57,620 --> 00:58:59,205
恩，好险啊。
Well, that's cutting it close.

1043
00:59:01,416 --> 00:59:03,793
这就是我叫你要跟紧我的原因，谢尔曼。
This is why I ask you to obey me, Sherman.

1044
00:59:05,295 --> 00:59:09,090
因为我是你的父亲，我的工作就是保护你的安全。
Because I'm your father, and it's my job to keep you safe.

1045
00:59:10,342 --> 00:59:13,303
但你确定古宁恩夫人不会把我从你身边带走？
But are you sure Ms. Grunion won't take me away?

1046
00:59:15,055 --> 00:59:16,931
只要我还在你身边就不会。
Not as long as I'm around.

1047
00:59:29,194 --> 00:59:30,403
皮博迪先生！
Mr. Peabody!

1048
00:59:30,445 --> 00:59:31,946
救命！
Help me!

1049
00:59:32,781 --> 00:59:33,782
佩妮！
Penny!

1050
00:59:41,331 --> 00:59:43,249
闻闻我的胜利！
Smell my victory!

1051
00:59:43,291 --> 00:59:44,876
闻一下！
Smell it!

1052
00:59:44,918 --> 00:59:47,295
嘿！那是我的座驾！
Hey! That's my ride!

1053
00:59:54,052 --> 00:59:55,178
皮博迪先生…
Mr. Peabody...

1054
00:59:55,220 --> 00:59:56,471
快点！
hurry!

1055
00:59:59,391 --> 01:00:00,558
我拿走了。
I'll take that.

1056
01:00:48,398 --> 01:00:50,191
你做到了，谢尔曼！
You did it, Sherman!

1057
01:00:50,233 --> 01:00:51,443
皮博迪先生干的。
Mr. Peabody helped.

1058
01:00:51,484 --> 01:00:54,863
现在，咱们去WABAC那里吧，回家，给佩妮的父母解除催眠…
Now, let's get to the WABAC, go home, un-hypnotize Penny's parents...

1059
01:00:54,904 --> 01:00:56,239
完成晚餐派对，吃我的火焰冰激凌…
finish that dinner party, eat my Baked Alaska...

1060
01:00:56,281 --> 01:00:57,642
顺便把古宁恩夫人的裤子一起迷倒…
charm the pants off Ms. Grunion...

1061
01:00:57,657 --> 01:01:00,118
然后确保这件事从没发生过。
and make sure none of this ever happens in the first place.

1062
01:01:00,160 --> 01:01:02,078
听起来很棒。
Sounds good.

1063
01:01:02,120 --> 01:01:03,121
我来了。
I'm in.

1064
01:01:07,125 --> 01:01:08,168
谢尔曼！
Sherman!

1065
01:01:08,585 --> 01:01:10,295
-佩妮！         -谢尔曼，不！
- Penny!        - Sherman, no!

1066
01:01:29,064 --> 01:01:30,607
皮博迪先生…
Mr. Peabody...

1067
01:01:31,441 --> 01:01:33,318
皮博迪先生？
Mr. Peabody?

1068
01:01:34,402 --> 01:01:36,029
皮博迪先生！
Mr. Peabody!

1069
01:01:37,781 --> 01:01:39,699
皮博迪先生！
Mr. Peabody!

1070
01:01:41,409 --> 01:01:42,702
爸爸！
Dad!

1071
01:01:53,129 --> 01:01:57,092
皮博迪先生！我应该怎么办？我应该怎么办？
Mr. Peabody! What should I do? What should I do?

1072
01:02:00,428 --> 01:02:02,806
你什么都做不了，谢尔曼。
There's nothing you can do, Sherman.

1073
01:02:05,892 --> 01:02:07,894
我只想回家。
I just want to go home.

1074
01:02:10,105 --> 01:02:11,231
家。
Home.

1075
01:02:12,482 --> 01:02:13,858
就是那个了。
That's it.

1076
01:02:14,359 --> 01:02:16,111
我有主意了。
I got an idea.

1077
01:02:16,403 --> 01:02:17,946
快点！
Come on!

1078
01:02:19,698 --> 01:02:20,949
我们要去哪？
Where are we gonna go?

1079
01:02:20,990 --> 01:02:22,283
我们回家。
We're going home.

1080
01:02:22,325 --> 01:02:24,369
只有一个人可以帮助我们…
There's only one person who can help us...

1081
01:02:24,411 --> 01:02:26,079
那就是皮博迪先生。
and that's Mr. Peabody.

1082
01:02:26,121 --> 01:02:28,832
你在说什么？这怎么可能？
What are you talking about? How is that even possible?

1083
01:02:28,873 --> 01:02:30,250
我们有时光机器，佩妮！
We've got a time machine, Penny!

1084
01:02:30,291 --> 01:02:34,045
我们可以设定它回到皮博迪先生还在家的时候。
I can set it so that we'll get home when Mr. Peabody is still there.

1085
01:02:34,421 --> 01:02:37,132
但我认为你不应该回到你存在的时空。
But I thought you're not supposed to go back to a time when you existed.

1086
01:02:37,173 --> 01:02:38,675
我们还有什么选择？
What choice do we have?

1087
01:02:39,342 --> 01:02:43,930
错误，你正试着要回到你所存在的时空。
<i>Error. You are attempting to travel to an era in which you exist.</i>

1088
01:02:43,972 --> 01:02:46,558
这可能会改变宇宙时空的结构。
<i>This could alter the fabric of space-time.</i>

1089
01:02:47,225 --> 01:02:50,103
错误。错误。
<i>Error. Error.</i>

1090
01:02:50,520 --> 01:02:51,980
抓紧了！
Hang on!

1091
01:02:59,821 --> 01:03:01,322
这太有趣了！！
This is fun!

1092
01:03:04,200 --> 01:03:07,495
这种简谱的家庭手工调味品，我喜欢把它叫做…
This is a little homespun concoction I like to call...

1093
01:03:08,246 --> 01:03:10,206
“躺在沙滩上的爱因斯坦”。
"Einstein on the Beach."

1094
01:03:10,248 --> 01:03:11,583
真棒。
Yummy.

1095
01:03:13,877 --> 01:03:15,128
至我们的孩子。
To the kids.

1096
01:03:15,170 --> 01:03:16,963
至我们的孩子！
To the kids!

1097
01:03:17,881 --> 01:03:19,507
皮博迪先生。
Mr. Peabody.

1098
01:03:19,549 --> 01:03:21,092
谢尔曼？佩妮？
Sherman? Penny?

1099
01:03:21,134 --> 01:03:22,510
我们可以跟你说句话么？
Can we talk to you a second?

1100
01:03:22,552 --> 01:03:23,595
当然可以。
Of course.

1101
01:03:23,636 --> 01:03:24,929
抱歉。
Excuse me.

1102
01:03:27,557 --> 01:03:29,601
我已经和佩妮的父母聊得来了。
I've really hit it off with your parents.

1103
01:03:29,642 --> 01:03:32,937
我想我们可以把这个夜晚打上“不合格的成功”的标签。
I think we can file this night under "Unqualified Success."

1104
01:03:32,979 --> 01:03:35,398
是我的话我就不会这么快给这个夜晚打标签了。
I'd hold off filing it just yet.

1105
01:03:35,440 --> 01:03:36,483
你说的是什么意思？
What do you mean?

1106
01:03:36,524 --> 01:03:38,985
为什么你们穿得像个古希腊人？
Why are you two dressed like ancient Greeks?

1107
01:03:39,027 --> 01:03:40,653
-你们用了WABAC!             -是的。
- You used the WABAC!       - I did.

1108
01:03:40,695 --> 01:03:42,322
我知道，那很糟糕！
I know, it's terrible!

1109
01:03:42,364 --> 01:03:43,490
但是为什么？
But why?

1110
01:03:43,531 --> 01:03:45,700
佩妮和我因为乔治华盛顿的事吵了起来。
Penny and I got into an argument about George Washington.

1111
01:03:45,742 --> 01:03:47,118
所以，我就让他带我去看了WABAC。
So, I made him show me the WABAC.

1112
01:03:47,160 --> 01:03:49,801
-我就把她落在古埃及了。                -我还和图特王订婚了。
- And I lost her in ancient Egypt.     - And I got engaged to King Tut.

1113
01:03:49,829 --> 01:03:51,623
-所以我就回来找你了。                 -然后机器没燃料了。
- So, I came back and got you.        - Then we ran out of gas.

1114
01:03:51,664 --> 01:03:53,416
-在佛罗伦萨。      -我们撞上了黑洞。
- In Florence.     - Went into a black hole.

1115
01:03:53,458 --> 01:03:55,168
然后你死在了古特洛伊。
And then you died in ancient Troy.

1116
01:03:55,210 --> 01:03:57,462
我死了？我才不信呢。
Died? I have a hard time believing that.

1117
01:03:57,504 --> 01:03:58,588
那是真的！
It's true!

1118
01:03:58,630 --> 01:04:01,216
但现在你在这里，一切都会好起来的。
But now you're here, and everything's gonna be okay.

1119
01:04:01,257 --> 01:04:03,385
我告诉过你你不应该回到你存在的时空来。
I told you never to come back to a time when you existed...

1120
01:04:03,426 --> 01:04:04,928
因为那样的话就会有两个你了！
because there would be two of you!

1121
01:04:04,969 --> 01:04:07,430
是啊，但另外一个我现在在古埃及。
Yeah, but the other one of me is in ancient Egypt.

1122
01:04:12,435 --> 01:04:13,561
你是谁？
Who are you?

1123
01:04:13,603 --> 01:04:15,397
他是你，但是是从别的时空来的。
He's you, but from another timeline.

1124
01:04:15,438 --> 01:04:18,650
但是我以为你说过不要回到你存在的时空来。
But I thought you said never to come back to a time when you existed.

1125
01:04:18,692 --> 01:04:20,360
-完全正确！     -我知道。
- Exactly!    - I know.

1126
01:04:21,111 --> 01:04:24,572
但我应该怎么办？皮博迪先生死在了古特洛伊。
But what was I supposed to do? Mr. Peabody died in ancient Troy.

1127
01:04:24,614 --> 01:04:25,657
死了？
Died?

1128
01:04:25,699 --> 01:04:27,283
我才不信呢。
I have a hard time believing that.

1129
01:04:27,325 --> 01:04:28,493
谢谢。
Thank you.

1130
01:04:28,535 --> 01:04:29,828
我们应该怎么办？
What are we going to do?

1131
01:04:30,120 --> 01:04:32,414
首先，两个谢尔曼都不可以在这里。
For starters, both Shermans can't stay here.

1132
01:04:32,455 --> 01:04:33,915
为什么？我们可以睡上下铺。
Why? We could get bunk beds.

1133
01:04:33,957 --> 01:04:35,166
我也在想这个。
I was thinking the same thing.

1134
01:04:35,208 --> 01:04:36,769
这好奇怪。就像我们是双胞胎一样！
That's so weird. It's like we're twins!

1135
01:04:36,793 --> 01:04:37,794
我也在想那个！
I was thinking that, too!

1136
01:04:39,462 --> 01:04:42,465
看见了吧？我们不可以把两个谢尔曼留在同一个时空。
You see? We can't have two Shermans in the same timeline.

1137
01:04:42,507 --> 01:04:46,052
这给宇宙时空施加了太多的张力。
It puts too much strain on the space-time continuum.

1138
01:04:46,094 --> 01:04:49,514
该怎么办？彼得逊一家不可以知道这件事。
What to do? The Petersons can't know any of this.

1139
01:04:49,556 --> 01:04:50,974
嘿，皮老大。
Hey, Pea-buddy.

1140
01:04:51,683 --> 01:04:52,767
嘿。
Hey.

1141
01:04:52,809 --> 01:04:53,935
还好吗？
How's it going?

1142
01:04:53,977 --> 01:04:56,563
佩蒂和我吃得很开心。
Patty and I are working up an appetite.

1143
01:04:57,105 --> 01:04:59,274
你厨房里的味道真是好闻啊。
The smells coming from your kitchen are yummy!

1144
01:04:59,315 --> 01:05:01,443
特别是那个火焰冰激凌。
Especially that Baked Alaska.

1145
01:05:02,027 --> 01:05:03,528
那么，你们在干什么呢？
So, what's going on here?

1146
01:05:03,570 --> 01:05:04,904
是啊，干嘛穿成这样？
Yeah, what's with the getups?

1147
01:05:05,363 --> 01:05:06,781
古罗马长袍派对！
Toga party!

1148
01:05:07,532 --> 01:05:08,742
古罗马长袍派对？
Toga party?

1149
01:05:08,783 --> 01:05:12,287
是啊，古罗马长袍派对！
Yes, it is a toga party!

1150
01:05:12,328 --> 01:05:13,663
那么，晚餐呢？
Well, what about dinner?

1151
01:05:13,705 --> 01:05:14,831
我饿死了。
I'm starving.

1152
01:05:14,873 --> 01:05:16,166
为什么不去餐厅…
Why don't we head into the dining room...

1153
01:05:16,207 --> 01:05:18,126
然后去大吃特吃一顿你一直在说的鹌鹑？
and tuck into those quails you've been yakking about?

1154
01:05:18,168 --> 01:05:19,336
-不！     -为什么不行？
- No!     - Why not?

1155
01:05:19,377 --> 01:05:23,173
因为呆在这里很有趣！
Because it's so fun right here!

1156
01:05:33,058 --> 01:05:34,225
古宁恩夫人！
Ms. Grunion!

1157
01:05:34,267 --> 01:05:36,561
多么棒啊！
How delightful.

1158
01:05:36,603 --> 01:05:37,964
我们在这儿很开心…
We were having such a good time...

1159
01:05:37,979 --> 01:05:39,356
我差点忘了你会来了。
I almost forgot you were coming.

1160
01:05:39,397 --> 01:05:41,149
干嘛不加入我们呢？
Why don't you join the party?

1161
01:05:41,191 --> 01:05:44,903
我来这儿不是来参加派对的。我在这儿是来做调查的。
I'm not here for a party. I'm here for the investigation.

1162
01:05:44,944 --> 01:05:48,323
行。你干嘛不在这开始你的调查呢？
Good. Why don't you start investigating over here?

1163
01:05:48,365 --> 01:05:51,451
或者这里，或者这里，或者这里…
Or here, or here, or here...

1164
01:05:51,493 --> 01:05:53,078
别乱挥你的手！
Stop waving your hands around!

1165
01:05:55,914 --> 01:05:56,956
谢尔曼？
Sherman?

1166
01:05:56,998 --> 01:05:58,667
等一下！那是不是…
Wait! Is that...?

1167
01:05:58,917 --> 01:06:00,585
谢尔曼！
Sherman!

1168
01:06:00,627 --> 01:06:03,797
两个谢尔曼？这是怎么了，皮博迪？
<i>Dos Shermanos?</i> What's going on here, Peabody?

1169
01:06:07,634 --> 01:06:08,927
每个人都别动！
Nobody move!

1170
01:06:08,968 --> 01:06:12,305
谢尔曼，我要在你碰到自己之前把你带走。
Sherman, I've got to get you out of here before you touch yourself.

1171
01:06:14,307 --> 01:06:16,476
皮博迪先生！你没死！
Mr. Peabody! You didn't die!

1172
01:06:16,518 --> 01:06:18,103
我当然没死。
Of course I didn't die.

1173
01:06:18,144 --> 01:06:19,396
谢谢。
Thank you.

1174
01:06:19,437 --> 01:06:21,439
嘿。你是怎么回来的？
Hey. How did you get back?

1175
01:06:21,481 --> 01:06:23,233
其实，在经过几次失败的尝试之后…
Well, after a few failed experiments...

1176
01:06:23,274 --> 01:06:25,610
我把骨头，石头，还有牦牛的脂肪…
I hit upon a combination of bones, stone and yak fat...

1177
01:06:25,652 --> 01:06:27,654
组合起来造了个原始版的WABAC。
and constructed a rudimentary WABAC.

1178
01:06:27,696 --> 01:06:28,905
你知道老话说得好…
You know what they say...

1179
01:06:28,947 --> 01:06:32,283
“如果一开始你没有成功，那就再试一次。”
"If at first you don't succeed, Troy, Troy again."

1180
01:06:32,325 --> 01:06:35,120
没有时间让你再说双关语了！即使你说得还不错。
This is no time for puns! Even good ones.

1181
01:06:35,161 --> 01:06:36,621
佩妮，谢尔曼，快点！
Penny, Sherman, quickly!

1182
01:06:36,871 --> 01:06:38,790
你们哪里都不准去。
You're not going anywhere.

1183
01:06:38,832 --> 01:06:41,209
我已经找到了足够多的理由把这个男孩…
I've seen quite enough to remove the boy...

1184
01:06:41,251 --> 01:06:43,795
这两个男孩，都带走。
both boys, from this home.

1185
01:06:43,837 --> 01:06:46,840
